title: poor man's cake
directions: Cook raisins in water for 10 minutes.
Remove and let cool. Mix oil and oleo with sugar and add to cooled raisins.
In a large bowl, sift flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix in cooled raisin mixture.
Add the nuts and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff with 1/4 cup sugar. Mix cheese, sugar and flour until smooth. Mix in all ingredients, except egg whites.
Fold in egg whites. If batter is too stiff, add another egg yolk or rum.
Grease and flour spring-form pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and toss first 5 ingredients, then mix together mayonnaise, Equal and vinegar; pour over broccoli.
Better to refrigerate overnight.
Re-toss before serving.
May use more mayonnaise if more broccoli is used.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and butter in large saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to full rolling boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until cool or proper consistency to drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: barbecue tuna(lo-cal)
directions: Simmer all ingredients until celery and bell pepper turn color, about 10 or 15 minutes.

title: reva's crock-pot deer
directions: Mix flour, mustard and some salt and pepper.
Roll deer in mixture.
Brown half of deer in large skillet.
Put in crock-pot. Put part of onions over deer.
Brown remaining deer.
Add to pot. Cover with remaining onions.
Mix soup and broth together.
Add Worcestershire sauce to soup.
Pour over deer.
Cook 10 to 12 hours on low.

title: easy quiche(low cholesterol)
directions: Combine liquid ingredients and spices.
Place seafood and cheese in pastry shell.
Pour liquid mixture over contents.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and mayonnaise with shredded shrimp. Add finely chopped onion and shredded cheese. Mix well. Salt may be added to taste. Refrigerate before serving.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until forms soft ball, then add chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Add nuts, if desired. Pour into 9 x 13-inch foil lined pan.
Let harden and cut into squares.

title: crabmeat spread appetizer
directions: Mix together and spread on crackers.

title: sherried beef
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven. Cover and bake for 3 hours.
Serve with dumplings, noodles or rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spring punch
directions: Can use frozen lemonade or powdered mix to make 2 quarts.

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper; brown in butter on both sides.
Remove chops from skillet; set aside.
Spread potatoes, carrots and onions evenly in skillet.
Place pork chops on top of vegetables.
Combine water, gravy mix and garlic salt; pour into skillet.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican blt
directions: Wrap all ingredients in shell.
Warm in microwave for 30 seconds and serve.

title: beef and bean chimichangas
directions: Brown ground beef in medium skillet over medium-high heat. Drain.
Remove beef from skillet; set aside.
Place 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute over medium heat until onion is tender.
Stir in ground beef, tomatoes, salsa, chili powder, coriander, thyme, salt, cayenne and cumin.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes, or until mixture is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in refried beans.
Heat 2 inches oil in deep fryer or large saucepan to 375° (a wok works well).

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Cover with a layer of Cool Whip, a layer of sliced bananas, a layer of crushed pineapple and a layer of strawberries (if desired).
On top spread a layer of Cool Whip with chopped pecans mixed in.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add frozen strawberries, bananas and pineapple.
Pour half the mixture into dish; chill until very firm.
Spread sour cream over congealed mixture; add remaining gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes nine servings.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Cook the raisins with 2 cups water; cook and cool.
Mix the sugar, lard, 1 cup cold water, soda, flour, salt and cinnamon. Mix all ingredients.
Add raisins.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: corn bread
directions: Cook all the ingredients as mush. Cool.

title: corn pudding or scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs and milk. Add cornstarch and other ingredients (add peppers last). Place in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until firm.

title: sweet-n-sour spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan until mixture thickens.
Brown ribs at 425° for 45 minutes.
Drain and reduce heat to 350°.
Use 1/2 sauce and cook 30 minutes. Turn spareribs, use remaining sauce and cook 45 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken dijon and vegetables
directions: Spread mayonnaise on both sides of fish.
Add oregano, seasoned salt, minced onion, bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake approximately 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
(Spray pan with Pam.)

title: chili(makes 3 servings)
directions: Heat oil in frying pan. Cook beef until lightly browned. Push to one side of pan. Add onion and celery. Cook until soft. Drain excess fat. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes. This is very good reheated.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Cook noodles for 3-4 minutes, rinse with cold water.
Add a tablespoon sesame oil.
Mix next 10 ingredients together.
Pour over noodles, add chicken, peas, olives and water chestnuts. Serve chilled.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after adding each.
Sift all dry ingredients together three times; add to other mixture along with milk to which has been added the vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Combine cereal crumbs and seasoning.
Beat oil into egg whites.
Roll chicken pieces in egg mixture, then in crumbs. Spread out on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon jello rainbow cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, Jell-O, water, oil, flavoring and eggs. Mix well.
Divide batter into three separate bowls and color each bowl of batter with a different color of food coloring.
Pour batter alternately into greased angel food cake pan.
Swirl the batter with a spatula.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use a glaze icing on top.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook at medium heat until it starts to bubble, then turn to low and cook for 15 minutes.
Let cool; store in 1 gallon jug or other suitable container.
Need not be refrigerated.
When used in cooking meat, mix sauce half and half with vinegar.
Great for dipping meat or cooking.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: Slice one
roll
of cookies and place in bottom of pan. Beat cream
cheese, sugar and eggs together.
Pour in pan over layer of cookies.
Slice
second roll of cookies and place on top of cream cheese layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spam casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until tender.
Make a layer of potatoes, layer Spam and then another of potatoes.
Then layer of Spam, then layer of onions.
Mix can of mushroom soup and milk together.
Pour over all layers. Cook at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs in a shallow dish using a fork.
Beat in salt, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Preheat griddle to 360°.
Brush with butter.
Quickly dip bread, one slice at a time, into egg mixture to coat both sides.
Brown on griddle, turning once.
Serve at once.

title: four step chocolate dessert
directions: Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Place
crackers
on
cookie
sheet
lined with aluminum foil. Mix
brown sugar and margarine in saucepan and bring to boiling point.
Pour over crackers.
Sprinkle pecans on top of crackers, bake
for 5 minutes
at
Sprinkle
chocolate chips over crackers and spread when melted.
Put in refrigerator until cooled and break into pieces.

title: toad in the hole
directions: Lightly grease a skillet.
Add sausages and cook gently, until lightly browned on all sides.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs well. Add milk, flour and salt.
Beat until smooth and pour over sausages in skillet.
Bake 25 minutes until batter is browned and set.

title: cappuccino
directions: Combine milk, chocolate, sugar and coffee in 4-cup glass measure.
Cook on High (maximum power) 2 minutes.
Stir.
Cook on High (maximum power) 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Divide among 4 mugs.
Top each with dollop of whipped cream before serving.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg if desired.
Makes 4 servings.
Total cooking time:
3 1/2 minutes.

title: easy mexican dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and stir in salsa until smooth.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind the Oreo cookies.
Cream together the butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Cream together the milk, Cool Whip and pudding.
Mix both cream mixtures together.

title: mucho mocha
directions: Stir chocolate and coffee in a mug containing brandy and milk. Heat (uncovered) in a microwave oven, about 1 1/2 minutes or until hot.
Stir and top with whipped cream.

title: beer burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 6 patties. Grill 4 to 6 minutes on each side, depending on desired degree of doneness.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour and nuts.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch dish and cook at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip until creamy.
Spread over crust.
Mix chocolate pudding as directed on box.
Spread over cream mixture. Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts; refrigerate.

title: chicken ragout with cheddar cheese dumpling
directions: Arrange carrots and pepper strips in a steam basket.
Place over boiling water.
Cover and steam for 8 minutes or until tender.
Set aside.

title: sausage bread
directions: Remove sausage from casing.
Saute in frying pan. Chop as small as possible.
Chop all vegetables as small as possible. (I use the food processor for the vegetables and sausage.)

When the sausage is almost cooked thoroughly, add onions, mushrooms and peppers. Drain mixture in colander to remove as much grease as possible. Shape pizza dough into rectangle (stretching as large as possible).
Spread mixture over dough.
Spread cheese over mixture.
Roll dough, stretching it as you roll it (trying to make it thinner).

Place on greased and floured (I use corn meal) pizza pan (the one with holes is best) and cook at 350° for 40 minutes. If dough has not browned, brush with a little egg white or oil. Cook another 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let cool down a few minutes. Slice and serve.

title: twinkies
directions: Combine milk and flour; cook until thick.
Chill.
Combine with Crisco, butter, salt, vanilla and sugar.
Beat until sugar dissolves and filling is light and fluffy.
Bake Duncan Hines yellow cake mix as directed.
Chill.
Split cake horizontally. Spread filling between the 2 layers.
Slice into bars.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Chill.

title: aunt pat's easy truffles
directions: Combine frosting and confectioners sugar in large bowl.
Stir with wooden spoon until well blended.
Cover each of 36 pecan halves with 1 tablespoon candy mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls; set aside.
Chop remaining nuts.
Place chocolate chips and shortening in a 2-cup glass microwave dish for 2 minutes on Medium heat; stir until smooth.
Dip one candy ball into hot chocolate mixture until completely covered.
Remove with fork and sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Allow to set, makes 36.

title: eggnog pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with eggnog, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in coconut and flavorings. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely before storing.

title: fast yeast rolls to make ahead
directions: Mix melted margarine with sugar.
Add warm water which has had yeast dissolved in it.
Add beaten egg.
Add flour.
Put light lid on bowl and refrigerate.
Spoon into greased muffin tins as needed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 36 muffins.

title: deep fried eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant; cut in half lengthwise and then into 1/2-inch wide slices.
Sprinkle with salt.
Set aside for 15 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat together the flour, milk, 1/3 cup water, 2 tablespoons peanut oil, cumin, onion salt and cayenne. Fold in egg whites.
Dip in eggplant slices and deep fry at 375° for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain and serve hot.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together in large mixing bowl. Add the next 4 ingredients and mix well. Fold in apples and nuts. Spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Mix together cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: robin's eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip eggplant slices into flour, then into eggs and then into bread crumbs.
Heat 1/4 cup oil in large skillet.
Brown eggplant slices in hot oil on one side.
Turn and brown on other side.
Add oil as needed.
Drain eggplant on paper towels.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Combine and beat well.
Pour in casserole dish.

title: missouri biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 450 degrees.
In a large mixing bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the oil and milk.
Beat until mixture clings together.
Pinch off portions and roll in balls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Flatten slightly. Melt the butter in a 7 inch skillet.
Place each biscuit in the butter and then turn it over so that each side is buttered.
Bake for about 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot. Yield: about 8 biscuits.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecan chips together.
Press into 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip* together and spread over first layer.
Mix pudding with milk; pour over second layer.
Top with more Cool Whip and pecan halves.

title: buttermilk coconut pies
directions: Separate egg yolks and freeze egg whites for later use.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Add melted margarine and stir. Add coconut.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk.
Mix well and pour into pie shells.
Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Cook slowly for 30 to 45 minutes on baking rack on lower level of oven.
Makes 2 pies. Allow to brown evenly on top.

title: homemade southern pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Beat eggs into creamed mixture, one at a time. Add rest of ingredients. Pour mixture into pie crust and bake in a 325° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: italian pasta bake
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain. Stir in pasta, sauce and 1/2 cup of Parmesan. Spoon into 13 x 9 baking dish. Top with Mozzarella cheese and remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk gradually.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens (3 to 5 minutes). Add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks.
Stir well and add to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and 1/2 can coconut.
Pour in pie shell. Top with meringue made of egg whites, cream of tartar and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° until meringue browns.

title: mexican pico de gallo (salsa)
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Stir to combine. Refrigerate at least 30 minutes before serving to blend flavors.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Slice onions and separate into rings.
Add bacon bits and mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: pepperoni eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl. Scramble eggs in pan. Continue until done.

title: tiramisu
directions: Break the eggs, separating yolks in a bowl and whites in another.
Whisk the Mascarpone until smooth, using a wood spoon. (This step may not be necessary as American Mascarpone usually comes smooth.)
Whisk the yolks with the sugar, then add the Mascarpone and fold together until you get a homogenous cream. Fold in the brandy and Marsala wine with the cream.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold them into the cream.

title: judith ann's potato casserole
directions: Crumble Tater Tots in baking dish. Saute onion and bell pepper with 1/4 cup butter.
Mix mushroom soup, cheese soup, salt and sour cream with onion and bell pepper.
Pour over Tater Tots. Top with corn flakes or Rice Krispies.
Drizzle 1/4 cup butter over corn flakes. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale.
Freeze until slushy.
At serving time, add to punch bowl and slowly pour in ginger ale.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Put berries and lemon juice in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, butter, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Spoon this mix over blueberries.
Mix 3/4 cup of sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Pour over dough and pour 1 cup of hot water over all. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: uncle charlie's irish cream
directions: Dissolve instant coffee in hot water, set aside.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer pie filling and pineapple in ungreased cake pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch) or tube pan.
Sprinkle cake mixture over this, next a layer of nuts.
Slice butter and put on nuts.
Do not stir or mix. Bake at 325° to 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: bearden chili
directions: Saute beef and onion just until red is gone.
Drain fat.
Add ingredients as listed.
Cook 3 hours.
Do not undercook; stir frequently the last hour.
Freezes well.
Can be served over spaghetti with grated cheese and extra chopped onion, if desired.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies(avoid the heat)
directions: In small bowl, combine oats, coconut, walnuts and set aside. In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil, 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: vanilla-butter and nut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk alternating.
Fold in flavoring and nuts by hand (cherries, too, if wanted).

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Measure 1/2 cup and blend into Cool Whip with sugar. Tint to desired shade with food coloring.
If necessary, chill Cool Whip mixture until firm enough to mold.
Spread over bottom and up sides of crumb crust.
Stir strawberries into remaining thickened gelatin and gently spoon on top of Cool Whip mixture. Chill at least 3 hours.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in two layers.
When cool, split layers to make four layers.
Mix coconut, sour cream and sugar.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups of mixture and spread the rest over the cake layers.

Mix the reserved 1 1/2 cups of the coconut mixture with Cool Whip and spread over top and sides. Refrigerate for three days before cutting.	Use Duncan Hines butter cake mix and an extra pack of coconut to spread over top and sides of cake.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in unbaked pie shell in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream after cutting.

title: piccalilli
directions: Mix together green tomatoes, red pepper, green peppers, onions and pickling salt.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Drain well.

title: frijoles de olla
directions: Clean and soak beans.
Drain, rinse and place in large saucepan; cover with hot water.
Bring to a boil.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 4 to 6 hours or until beans are tender, adding water as needed to cover beans.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Stir
first
2 ingredients well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well, then fold in berries.
(May
use
blueberries,
peaches, blackberries, etc.) Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: orange juice slush
directions: Put ingredients in blender and mix until ice is crushed good.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine cream of potato soup, vegetables and chicken and pour into crust lined pie plate.
Cover with second crust.
Slit crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mounds
directions: Mix sugar, butter, coconut, Eagle Brand milk and nuts in big bowl.
Use hands to mix.
Shape into bars.
Wrap in wax paper and freeze overnight.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, Cheez Whiz and mayonnaise together with half the jar of Bac*Os.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with remaining half jar of Bac*Os.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: corn and onion casserole
directions: Crush half the onions.
Saute green pepper in margarine until soft.
Add corn, pimento, egg and crushed onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until firm. Sprinkle remaining onions on top.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: pickled beets
directions: Put beets in jars. Bring vinegar, spice and sugar to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes. Then pour over beets.

title: wedding punch
directions: Ream lemons and oranges; remove seeds.
Combine sugar and water and bring to boil.

title: fried potatoes and onions
directions: Place chopped potatoes in microwave dish.
Cover and cook until done.
May need to stir occasionally to separate since they are dry.
Meanwhile, saute onions on low heat in olive oil until desired doneness; we like ours crisp.
When potatoes are done, pour off any liquid that may have cooked out.
Turn burner to medium high heat.
Add potatoes to onions and brown.
Delicious and great without all the fat.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion with butter; set aside.
Mix squash with 2 eggs. Put in soup then corn bread.
Add onion mixture.
Pour in casserole dish and bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chris' potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and corn flakes.
Pour in a large casserole dish.
Top with the corn flakes tossed with the melted margarine.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy chicken salad
directions: Simmer chicken, covered in water 15 to 20 minutes or until tender. Cut into 1/4 inch slices. Arrange chicken, tomatoes and pea pods on individual lettuce-lined plates. Stir in remaining ingredients in 1 quart saucepan over low heat until cheese is melted. Pour over chicken. Makes four servings. 230 calories per serving.

title: oven chicken salad
directions: Combine celery, onion, chicken and almonds.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, salt and pepper and mix into chicken mixture.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; sprinkle with cheese and top with potato chips.

title: breakfast crumb cake
directions: Mix the sugar, Crisco, flour and spices together as for a pie dough.
Set
aside	1/2 cup of mixture for topping.
To the remainder,	add
the
egg, molasses, sour milk and baking soda. Mix
together.
Bake
in
an 8 x 8-inch square pan; top with the 1/2
cup of crumbs that you set aside.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: taco twist casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce and green pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Combine cooked macaroni, 1/2 cup cheese and sour cream; place on bottom of 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Top with meat mixture and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Add flour.
Divide dough into 24 balls and press into tart pans, indenting center.

title: english lemon curd
directions: Melt margarine and sugar.
While this is melting beat eggs and add slowly to mixture.
Boil 5 minutes and add lemon juice.
Boil another 5 minutes.

title: creole green beans
directions: Brown bacon and set aside.
In small amount of bacon fat, saute onions and green pepper.
Add beans and tomatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top and serve. Goes great with any pork.

title: rice pudding
directions: To cooked rice, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a lightly greased 2 1/2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with Cool Whip.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix together.
Stir every day with wooden spoon.
Keep it at room temperature in a loosely covered glass jar (1 gallon or larger).
Put lid on 1/2 turn.
Fruit may bubble, but this is natural; do not refrigerate.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice from crushed pineapple can.
(Do not boil.)
Mix jello in and stir for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip, walnuts and cottage cheese.
Chill before serving.

title: bow tie pasta salad
directions: First, you cook your pasta and then your vegetables.
After they have both been cooked, drain.
You then add your pasta and vegetables with remaining ingredients in a large bowl and stir all together.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.

title: creamy cabbage slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir.
Serve.
Can roll up in cabbage leaves and serve.

title: green beans with ham
directions: Drain cooked beans.
Melt butter in a large skillet. Saute garlic and ham until soft.
Add beans, salt and pepper.
Cut tomatoes into thin wedges. Cook 5 to 10 minutes to mix flavors, tossing gently. Serves 6.

title: perfect peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
In large bowl, with electric mixer on medium
speed beat butter, peanut butter, granulated sugar and half
of the brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat in.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and
salt.
With
mixer
at
low
speed beat into butter mixture until blended.
Sprinkle remaining brown sugar on top of
dough and
fold
in
lightly
so sugar granules are still visible.
Roll into
balls
and
press out with fork to about 1/4-inch thick. Bake 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies, 73 calories a cookie.

title: million dollar pudding(diet)
directions: Prepare pudding with whipping cream and cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, Equal, pineapple and nuts together.
Add cold pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: spaghetti salad(spaghetti insalata)
directions: Mix all ingredients
together,
except
spaghetti.
Let mixture marinate for 5 minutes.
Add cooked, cooled spaghetti. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
This
is great for a buffet and everyone loves it.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Allow butter to come to room temperature.
Cream together butter, peanut butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls and place about 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork in crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut in bottom of pan. Sprinkle nuts over coconut.
Mix German chocolate cake according to directions.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Mix cream cheese and margarine.
Pour (spoon) powdered sugar over cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
This recipe will
serve 12 people.

title: potato kugel
directions: Grate potatoes and onions in food processor.
Add eggs, matzo meal, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable oil.
Heat oil in oven.
Pour mixture in hot pan.
Put back in oven at 375°.
Turn oven down to 350° after 1/2 hour.

title: honeyed carrots
directions: Rinse and trim carrots.
Cook in a small amount of boiling water for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Melt margarine in a skillet over medium heat.
Add sugar, honey and carrots.
Reduce heat to low and cook, turning carrots frequently, until well glazed.
Serve immediately; sprinkle with parsley.

title: coconut-cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and cream cheese; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, stirring just until blended.
Stir in coconut and remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Add zucchini (squeeze out any excess juice) and pecans.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: wild rice dressing
directions: Wash rice several times, drain and add 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer for 1 hour, or until rice is tender.
Add water as it boils off and is absorbed.

title: low-fat veggie soup
directions: Simmer veggies until tender.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together well.
Add flour with baking powder and salt.
Add milk with margarine melted in it.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: french onion soup
directions: Combine oil and butter in a large Dutch oven. Heat until butter melts.
Add onions and saute until tender. Add broth, sugar, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer soup mixture 20 minutes.
Place toasted bread in individual soup bowls.
Add soup and top with cheese slice.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: rice and ham rolls for 8
directions: Mix rice with 1/2 cup green onion and parsley.	Combine rice with chicken and shrimp.
Set aside.
Saute in butter the mushrooms
and
other
1/2 cup of onion.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper,
chicken broth, half and half and cheese.
After sauce has thickened, add wine slowly.
Combine 1 cup of sauce with 2 cups of	rice mixture.
Place about 2 tablespoons down center of
ham slices.
Place remaining rice in bottom of buttered 13 x
x 2-inch
pan.
Roll up ham and place seam side down on rice	bed. Spoon
remaining
sauce over rolls.
Cover tightly and
chill overnight.	Bake
at
350°	for
about
15 minutes covered and 10 minutes uncovered.

title: band dessert surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve later.

title: garlic toast
directions: Soften butter and add seasonings.
Slice French bread in half the long way, then in half again, then in half again and again! Butter 3 sides.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Bread must not touch during baking.
Store in airtight container.

title: rice dish
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Put all together in large bowl.
Mix. Put in baking dish; cover.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Heat 1 quart water to boiling.
Add noodles and salt.
Then pour into strainer to drain.
Grease casserole dish.
Drain peas and add mushroom soup from can to bowl.
Add milk to soup and mix well.
Arrange in layers in casserole dish.
Half of noodles, half tuna, half peas and mushroom soup.
Then do the other half by layers again.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate coconut mounds
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, coconut, vanilla and sweetened condensed milk. Mold into pieces (any size). Place an almond or other nut on top of each. Refrigerate overnight on a cookie sheet. In the morning, melt the paraffin and chocolate chips together over very low heat. Dip candy pieces into the chocolate mixture and place them on wax paper. Refrigerate until set.

title: pumpkin spice sweet potato balls
directions: Mash cooked yams with a fork.
Stir in spices.
Stir in milk

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Beat egg; stir in milk and shortening.
Add flour mixture all at once and beat until well blended.
Fold in eggplant.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot deep fat.
Brown quickly on both sides and serve hot.

title: fruity cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese in large bowl until smooth.
Beat in gelatin until well blended.
Form mixture into 5-inch round.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill about 1 hour.
Remove plastic wrap. Press pecans gently around edges of cheese round.
Serve with fruit, cookies and crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: easy vegetable-beef soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, simmer beef shanks with the water, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Chill beef and broth. Remove and discard fat.

Cut meat in small sizes. In saucepan, combine meat, 3 cups broth and remaining ingredients. Bring to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until vegetables are tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: roy's chocolate pie
directions: Mix and cook 10 minutes.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Brown sausage and mix accordingly.
I usually add melted butter and water if needs to be more moist.
If the dressing seems moist and tastes good uncooked, you've done it correctly.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: mama's chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil the chicken seasoned with chicken granules, bell pepper and onion flakes until done.
De-bone chicken.
Strain broth and return to boiling.
Drop dumplings into boiling broth and boil 10 minutes.

title: hamwiches
directions: Combine butter, mustard, onion and poppy seed.
Spread this mixture on buns and add ham and cheese slices.
Wrap sandwiches in aluminum foil and freeze.
To serve, heat (still wrapped) in 400° oven for 35 minutes.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: In a mixing bowl put eggs.
Add sugar, salad oil and extract. Mix thoroughly.
Sift flour, salt and soda.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package and drain. Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs. Pour into a well-buttered baking dish. Sprinkle the cracker crumbs on top and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: *Add sugar if using peaches or strawberries.

title: broccoli tuna roll-ups
directions: Combine soup and milk; set aside.
Combine tuna, broccoli, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Stir in 3/4 cup soup mixture. Divide tuna mixture evenly on each tortilla and roll; place seam-side down in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir tomato into remaining soup and pour over tortillas.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip. Pour into a deep dish and sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Let stand about 1 hour before serving.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil brown sugar, white sugar and cream until forms firm ball when dropped in water. Remove and add margarine and vanilla. Beat until spreading consistency.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, flour,
jello
and
water.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating	after
each
addition.	Add
oil
and strawberries.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake
in tube pan in 350° oven for 40 minutes or in 9-inch layer pans for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan or tube pan.

Cream butter and cream cheese (these ingredients should be very soft). Add sugar and flavorings and mix well. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating until well mixed after each addition. Beat in cake flour until smooth, no longer.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tested done.

title: cream of potato soup(serves 100)
directions: Put diced potatoes, celery and onions in pots.
Add enough water to cover vegetables by about 1-inch.
Add salt. Cook until tender.
Pour off liquid to about 1/2 in each pot.
Save some of the liquid for thinning soup later. Add evaporated milk and cook until slightly thickened and very hot.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 sticks or margarine to each pot and some finely chopped parsley. Taste for salt.
As the soup stands, it will thicken.

title: chicken balls
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter; add parsley and green onions. Cook one minute.
Blend in flour; stir in milk, salt and hot sauce. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in chicken.
Form balls using 1 tablespoon of mixture for each ball.
Beat eggs until well mixed; dip balls into bread crumbs, into eggs and then into bread crumbs again.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Fill a large saucepan or deep fryer to mid level with oil and heat to 350°.
Fry a few balls at a time until golden brown (2 to 3 minutes).
Makes two dozen.

title: egg and mushroom souffle
directions: Spread in order given:
croutons,
sausage and cheese in a
9-inch pan layered.
Beat
eggs.
Add
milk
and
dry mustard. Pour over cheese.
Cover
and
place
in refrigerator overnight. The next morning, put sliced mushrooms on top.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with milk.
Pour over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
A
very
good
recipe for Christmas morning or when you have guest and don't want to spend a lot of time in the kitchen.

title: peach fruit salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients. Stir in the pie filling.
Add the marshmallows.
Add the Cool Whip.
Add the bananas just before serving.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Combine sugar and vanilla in bowl; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; blend into egg mixture.
Fold in nuts and fruit.
Turn into buttered 9-inch square baking pan; bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve plain or topped with whipped cream or ice cream.
Also excellent with vanilla pudding, hot or cold.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let chill at least 1 hour. Good as a dip for chips.

title: orange "n" nut parfaits
directions: In a medium bowl, combine milk and juice concentrate.
Mix well. Fold in whipped cream.
In a small bowl, stir together coconut, nuts and rind.
Layer filling and coconut mixture in parfait glasses, topping with coconut mixture.
Chill 2 hours.

title: easy banana pie
directions: Put bananas in pie crust.
Pour pudding, mixed per package instructions, over the bananas and top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: delicious cornbread
directions: Sift together cornmeal mix and flour.
Make a little well in the center and add egg, oil and sugar.
Beat this a little and add buttermilk; beat well.
If this is too stiff, add a little water to get it the consistency you want.
I don't like mine too stiff. Pour into an 8-inch black skillet that has been greased with Crisco and sprinkled with a little dry cornmeal.
Cook in 425° oven 25 to 30 minutes.
(Some of my friends say this is as good as cake.) Keeps well in the refrigerator in foil.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Prebake pastry crust until 3/4 done.
Pour apple mixture in crust.
Slice 1/2 stick oleo over mixture.
Top with additional pie crust, slit in several places, and add oleo slices.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender.

title: turtle cake
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt caramels with butter and evaporated milk.
Mix cake by directions.
Pour half of cake batter into floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with chocolate chips, pecans and caramel mixture.
Pour second half of batter over top.
Return to oven.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
May frost, if desired. Chocolate is good.

title: the best strawberry-rhubarb muffins
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil in separate bowl.
Stir into flour mixture until just moistened. Fold rhubarb and strawberries into batter.
Fill well buttered muffin tins 2/3 full.
Press a strawberry half into the top of each muffin and sprinkle with sugar generously.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cookie press cookies
directions: Fill barrel of cookie press with mixture and bake at 350° until set but not brown.
Carefully remove from pan.

title: stir-fry pancakes
directions: Pour all ingredients into a blender and blend well.
Melt 1/2 stick butter in an electric frying pan or large skillet.
Pour all of the batter into pan and stir while frying.
May sprinkle with powdered sugar or use syrup.

title: quiche
directions: Grease the pan.
Place cheese and bacon on the bottom of the pan; meanwhile, beat the eggs, salt, Bisquick and milk.
Pour over the cheese.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 400° in oven.

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Combine salmon, onion, cream cheese, lemon juice, pepper, milk and scallions in food processor.
Process until smooth.
Gently fold in 2 teaspoons caviar.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
(I put it in a mold.) May be prepared 2 days before serving.
Garnish with 1 teaspoon caviar and scallion greens. Serve with crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into 9 x 9-inch or 7 x 11-inch baking dish. Cook at 350° or until brown on top.

title: banana cake or cupcakes
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients.
Bake at 375° until done.
Can be made into cupcakes, too.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Combine vegetables in glass dish.
Mix other ingredients and bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute and pour immediately over vegetables.
Cover and chill.

title: patio potato salad
directions: Cook and stir first nine ingredients over low heat until thickened.
Remove from stove and blend in onion and mayonnaise. Cool.

title: caramel cream pie
directions: Spread 2 cups sugar in skillet.
Stir over low heat until sugar is melted and browned.
Cool slightly.
Blend flour into sugar.
Beat egg yolks; stir in milk.
Add to flour mixture, stirring, cook over low heat stirring constantly until thickened. Add butter and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add remaining sugar gradually beating until stiff and glossy.
Pour filling into pie shells.
Spread meringue over filling.
Bake at 350° until meringue is lightly brown.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain and rinse all fruit.
Combine with orange juice.
Add mayonnaise.
Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze in ice cube trays. Cut into cubes and serve in lettuce cups.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Grind together Spam and Velveeta cheese. Stir in chili, mixing thoroughly. Spread on English muffins. Broil until bubbly.

title: apple cottage pudding
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream the butter, vanilla, lemon rind and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cream until well blended.
Add egg and beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk until smooth batter forms.

title: three layer pie
directions: Combine flour, stick of melted butter and chopped pecans. Spread in 9 x 13 pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread on cooled crust.
Mix puddings with milk and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with grated Hershey bar.
Refrigerate.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Place pudding and pineapple with juice in bowl. Stir together. Add marshmallows (approximately 1 cup).
Then fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate before serving.

title: savory cabbage casserole
directions: Combine first five ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Place 1/2 rice in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer with cabbage mixture. Repeat layers.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Stir well.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplant thin.
Dip slices in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until brown; drain on paper towels. Layer eggplant, cheese and tomato sauce alternately in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: zesty meatballs
directions: In bowl, thoroughly mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, crumbs, egg, celery and 1/4 teaspoon ginger.
Shape into 50 meatballs.
Arrange in jelly roll pan.
Broil 4 inches from heat about 10 minutes or until done, turning once.
Drain.

title: super sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine margarine, oil and granulated sugar. Beat until creamy; add powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Sift soda, flour, cream of tartar and salt; add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes. Yields about 100 cookies.

title: rice with pigeon peas(arroz cun gandules)
directions: Cut ham into small squares.
Slice pimientos into small strips. In a high temperature pot, mix the sofrito, ham, oil, bacon (optional) and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, pimientos, olives, bay leaves (optional) broken in half and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add rice and enough water to cover.
Add salt if desired.
Cover pot and wait until water is dissolved. Turn the rice, lower temperature to medium and let cook for another 10 minutes.
Put one plantain leave over the rice to give it a turnover taste and lower temperature to low until rice is ready. Serves up to 20.

title: black bottoms
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients well, then stir in 1 cup of chocolate chips; set aside.
In separate bowl mix remaining ingredients. Beat well.
Fill baking cups* 1/3 full with chocoalte batter.
Top each with 1 heaping teaspoon of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes on cookie sheet.
Makes about 30.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Blend in flour, salt and pepper; cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat; stir in milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute. Add grated cheese. Can add more cheese for vegetables or potatoes if desired. Serves 1 cup.

title: cool eclair dessert
directions: Layer crackers on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Spread over crackers.
Layer remaining crackers on top.
Heat frosting in microwave until pourable and drizzle over crackers until covered.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: kid's choice casserole
directions: Chop hot dogs.	Mix all ingredients and place in an oven safe dish.
Cook uncovered for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 5.

title: glorious grahams
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line a cookie sheet with graham crackers close together.
Bring to a boil sugar and butter.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Cover graham crackers with chopped pecans.
Pour sugar/butter mixture over crackers.
Place in preheated oven for 9 minutes.
Separate onto waxed paper while warm.

title: dutch cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill.
Makes a little over a cup.
Peel cucumbers and thinly slice both.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add sour cream dressing.
Toss, chill and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Stir all ingredients with a large spoon until blended. Add blueberries last (fold in) so they don't tear up.
Oil muffin tins. Bake at 400° until golden brown.
So good.
These are also good with strawberries.

title: brown sugar & cinnamon butter
directions: In a small bowl beat all ingredients together until fluffy.

title: dump cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13 pan. Spread pineapple first, then cherry pie filling. Use your choice of yellow or white cake mix. Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the pineapple and pie filling. Pour melted butter over top. Sprinkle nuts over this. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease pan.
Pour rice over bottom of pan.
Place chicken, skin side up, over rice.
Mix mushroom soup with water; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Do not peek!

title: cheesy broccoli and chicken bake
directions: Cook broccoli using package directions.
Combine soup and sour cream in bowl; mix well.
Layer broccoli, soup mixture, rice, chicken, cheese and water chestnuts in medium baking dish.
Toss cracker crumbs with butter in bowl.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add stuffing; mix until stuffing is coated with margarine.
Put a thick layer of the mixture in casserole dish, saving some for the top.
Mix thoroughly the first 6 ingredients.
Pour on top of first layer.
Put the rest of the stuffing mixture on top; bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until bubbling and brown.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla extract.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Put chocolate in double boiler and melt.
(May use microwave oven to melt.)
Drop in peanuts and stir good.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool until set.
Store in airtight container.

title: "spice cake in a jar"
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add applesauce, water and eggs and mix well. Mix dry ingredients in another bowl and add to first mixture. Add nuts (or raisins), if desired. Spray wide-mouth

pint jars with Pam and fill about 1/2 full. This will fill 6 to 8 jars. Bake at 325° exactly 45 minutes. Remove jars one at a time and quickly screw the lid on each jar. Let set until ready to eat. When you use canning jar lids, this cake has a shelf life of one year.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Coat a medium saucepan with vegetable cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and saute 3 minutes or until tender.
Add flour, mustard and salt; stir well and cook an additional minute.
Remove from heat; gradually add milk and broth, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add cheeses and pepper, stirring until cheeses melt. Stir in sour cream.

title: italian chicken and spinach roll
directions: Pound out chicken breasts until about 1/8-inch thick.
Combine the remaining ingredients together.
Place about 1/3 cup of the mixture on chicken and spread out.
Roll chicken around spinach.

title: date nut bread
directions: Sprinkle baking soda over dates. Add water.
Let cool and mash.
Beat egg yolk and pour over sugar, salt and melted butter. Pour this over date mixture. Add flour and beat with spoon. Add vanilla and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg white.
Pour mixture into greased and floured bread pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Check with toothpick.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain off water.
Set aside 2 ounces Cheddar cheese.
Add rest of cheeses, butter and salt and stir until melted.
Put into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with milk.
Top with 2 ounces Cheddar.
Bake at 350° on top shelf for 45 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; combine with remaining ingredients. Place in large bowl; set in warm place to rise until double in bulk. Punch down; knead for a few minutes. Pinch off and form into rolls.
Let rise again, then bake for 5 minutes in 400° oven, then reduce to 350° and finish baking.

title: great banana muffins
directions: In large bowl blend yogurt, Fruit Sweet, margarine, applesauce and mashed banana.
Stir in flour and soda.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into batter.
Mix in rolled oats, cereal and raisins.
Spoon into 12 muffin cups which have been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Bake 20 minute at 350° or until firm.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour and sugar.
Add nuts.
Cut in oleo until crumbly.
Combine sugar, rhubarb and cinnamon.
Place 1/2 of crumbs in greased 8-inch pan.
Cover with rhubarb mixture.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Blend all the ingredients together except cucumbers.
Add cucumbers and mix well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: 90 minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine to 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Knead dough 2 to 3 minutes. Divide into 12 equal parts.
Shape into balls.
Place in greased 8-inch round pan.
Pour 1 inch boiling water into a large pan on bottom rack of oven.
Set rolls on rack above water.
Cover and close oven door.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Uncover rolls, remove water.
Turn oven to 375°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar, then add the vanilla and egg yolks and cream all together.
Add alternately the sifted flour, buttermilk and soda.
Then add the pecans and coconut. Beat 5 egg yolks until very stiff.
Fold in the batter by hand, very delicately.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) cake pans, greased and floured, at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and cook sweet potatoes in skins until tender.
Peel and slice into casserole dish.

title: chicken ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in mixer.
Stir in chicken.
Chill until firm.
Using spatula, form into 1 large or 2 small balls. Chill, then roll in bread crumbs.
Chill several hours.
Serve on crackers. Keep refrigerated.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all together.
Makes one large punch bowl.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Dice chicken.
Add soup, pimento and onion.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix with chicken mixture and place in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for another 15 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mediterranean pasta toss
directions: Prepare pasta as directed and drain.
Meanwhile, cook and stir red peppers, onion, garlic and pepper in hot oil until tender. Stir remaining ingredients.
Heat and toss with pasta.

title: whatever vegetable salad
directions: Mix vegetables, water chestnuts, pimentos, cheese and 1/2 can onions into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Then mix the milk with soup and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until carrots are tender.
Sprinkle remaining onions on top and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: sweet potato pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cream potatoes; add sugar and butter, eggs, milk, nutmeg, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until it browns.

title: poor man's filet mignon
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, plus 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce in large bowl.
Mix well.
Form into 12 separate thick patties. Wrap each patty with one slice bacon, secure with toothpick.
Bake on broiler pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Baste with barbecue sauce last 30 minutes.

title: cat leveen's original ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and vanilla.
Add cream, Eagle Brand milk and half and half.
Pour in container.
Add sweet milk to fill container.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken; salt and pepper.
Sprinkle rice over chicken. In large bowl, mix both soups, melted margarine and water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: soft cutout sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture and mix well.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Roll out on surface lightly coated with powdered sugar to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost with confectioners sugar icing and candy sprinkles.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter and pour fruit over batter.
Cook in moderate oven at 350° until done (30 to 40 minutes, approximately).

title: southern living potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice as thin as possible. Layer potatoes in a 9 x 13 buttered casserole dish. Add rest of ingredients and bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add vanilla.
Add sugar, gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Sift flour.
Measure.
Sift again with salt and add gradually to the sugar mixture.
Add pecans.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten cookies and bake in moderate 325° oven about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
While hot, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: bean supreme casserole
directions: *Beans can be bought with spice packet included, called bean soup mix.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar, butter, milk, salt, syrup and vanilla until soft ball stage is formed in tap water.
Add cut up dates and cook until dissolved.
Take off burner.
Then add pecans and beat until it thickens; transfer onto a large flour sack cup towel which has been wet in tap water and squeezed out very well.
Form a roll of this mixture and roll it in this towel.
Leave until cool and cutting stage.

title: lemon oat lacies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Cover and chill for 30 minutes.
Roll into 1-inch balls; flatten with powdered sugar dipped glass.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to rack; sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix together. Bake in 10-inch pie plate in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: nine bean soup
directions: *Some stores carry these in a mix ready to wash and soak.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix sugars and oil; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add zucchini, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in loaf pans.
Roll raisins in flour.
Drop on top.
Freeze well.

title: bill's bread pudding
directions: Break eggs in a 1-quart Pyrex baking dish.
Beat until frothy. Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat again.
Add milk, slowly, beating until well blended.
Break bread apart into 8 to 12 pieces and press them into the egg mixture with a fork.
Let them soak for a little bit.
Stir in raisins.
Sprinkle mixture lightly with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until set, puffy and golden.
Eat while warm.

title: dee's buns
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Put in the nuts, then frozen rolls. Sprinkle pudding over all of rolls.
Melt brown sugar, cinnamon and cube of margarine together; drizzle mixture over all.
Set pan on drain board overnight to rise.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cut beef into small pieces and layer in bottom of pan or crock-pot. Wrap each breast in 1 to 2 strips bacon. Place chicken on top of beef. Mix soup, sour cream and flour and pour mixture on top of chicken. If using crock-pot, allow to cook on low all day (put it in before work and have for supper).
If baking, use a moderate oven (350°) and bake slowly until done.

title: layered green salad
directions: Mix together 1 teaspoon sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and sprinkle over mayonnaise.
Last, sprinkle one package grated (8 ounce) Mozzarella cheese over mayonnaise and top with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.

title: loaf cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time; blend together. Mix in salt, flour and vanilla. Cook slowly for 1 hour at 250°.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt in large bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract until well blended.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until edge of cookies are golden brown. Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Makes about 18 macaroons.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Saute chopped onion; add spinach and stir.
Cool 5 minutes. Mix with Egg Beaters.
Can add mushrooms.
Place in a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jello popcorn
directions: Combine sugar, Karo syrup and Jell-O mix in heavy cooking pan. Bring to full rolling boil. Pour over popped corn.
Blend well until all the popcorn is coated. Shape into balls or leave as a crunch.

title: mint sauce
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a saucepan.
Heat gently for 1 minute.
Allow to stand for a couple of hours before serving.

title: wonderful wild rice, ham and cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion until tender.
Blend in flour, gradually.
Add broth.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens slightly.
Stir in rice and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend in half and half.
Add carrots, ham, cheese and almonds.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make roux with oil and flour, stirring constantly until dark brown.
Add celery, onions, bell pepper and garlic to roux and cook until tender.
Add roux and vegetables to stock and add okra. Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
Add shrimp about 10 minutes before serving.
Serve hot over rice.
Add gumbo file.
This recipe is also good using chicken.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Cook until crisp in microwave oven or fry until crisp.
Dice onion and green pepper; mix onion, green pepper, syrup, sugar and ketchup together, then pour into beans and mix well.
Pour bacon grease into beans and mix, then place the squares of bacon over the top of the beans.
Cook for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mrs. vaughan's indoor barbecue sauce
directions: Thinly slice the middle part of the lemon and juice the ends. Combine all ingredients in saucepan over very low heat.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown the
ground beef in the fat.
Add all ingredients and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: carrot ring bread
directions: Scrape	and
shred
carrots;
measure
by pressing into measuring cup.
In	large
mixing
bowl,
beat eggs.
Add oil, lemon juice
and onion powder or juice.
Add carrots.
Stir in flour, small amounts at a time.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Pour batter
in pan and bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream and marshmallows.
Drain juice from fruit and fold into sour cream and marshmallows.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with a small amount of mayonnaise. Add salt to taste. When ready to serve, add 1 small tomato, peeled, drained and diced. Chill and serve, or you may serve at once.

title: skillet mallow yams
directions: Drain yams; reserve 3/4 cup syrup. In a skillet, combine syrup, marshmallows, raisins, margarine and cinnamon.
Cook over low heat.
Stir constantly until mallows melted. Add yams. Simmer 15 minutes or until syrup thickens. Stir occasionally.

title: chicken n' biscuit
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Rinse green peas under running cold water to separate.
Drain.
Heat peas, chicken, soup, sour cream, 1/2 cup cold milk, salt and pepper.
Heat just to boiling, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat.
Keep warm while preparing biscuits.

title: reuben dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Put in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve on rye bread or with crackers.

title: macaroni and crabmeat salad
directions: Peel banana.
With a potato ball, scoop out balls from bananas and sprinkle with lemon juice to prevent discoloring.
Add portions of sliced pineapple; sprinkle with sugar and pour over a few spoonfuls of maraschino cherries.
Cover top with a topping of freshly grated coconut.
This gives a pink cocktail.
For lavender or purple, use grape juice.

title: grandma's always perfect apple pie
directions: Put apples in a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon on top.
In a medium bowl, mix butter, sugar, flour, egg and wheat germ together.
Spread over apples.
Bake, cool, serve and enjoy.

title: spinach-rice casserole
directions: Combine spinach, onion, cooked rice and rarebit.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Dot generously with butter.
Cover with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: greta's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together the brown sugar, white sugar and shortening.
Add the eggs.
Add the soda, dissolved in the hot water.
Add the flour, salt, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or less (until done).

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and place in a large 13 x 9-inch greased Pyrex dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
For the last 15 minutes, uncover and top with 2 cups crushed potato chips and 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Bake until brown.
Makes 14 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs. Add flour and fruit cocktail. Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: walnut and blue-cheese potato salad
directions: Heat a toaster oven to 325 degrees.
Bake walnuts 6 to 8 minutes until toasted.
Cool.
Meanwhile, combine potatoes and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil, and cook potatoes 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain in colander.
Whisk together oil, mayonnaise, chives, vinegar, salt, and sugar in a large bowl.
Gently stir in walnuts, drained potatoes, and cheese with a rubber spatula to combine.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel syrup
directions: Mix ingredients together in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil; reduce heat enough to keep boiling.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Put eggplant in one layer on a cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick coating.
Spread with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with crumbs. Bake 10 minutes at 475°; remove from oven.
Combine cottage cheese with egg and garlic salt.

title: chopped veal cutlets
directions: Stir egg, garlic and onion together. Combine bread crumbs and cheese. Spread some of the crumb mixture on wax paper. Take a handful of the meat mixture; press it on the crumbs. Sprinkle with additional crumbs and flatten the meat into a thin cutlet, using a spatula or the palm of your hand. Lift with a spatula onto a shallow nonstick cookie sheet which has been sprayed with cooking spray

for no-fat frying. Continue shaping and bread coating cutlets. Discard excess crumbs. Put the tray in a very hot oven that has been preheated to 450°. Bake 8 to 10 minutes, turning over. Garnish with lemon wedges and fresh parsley, if desired. Serves 4.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: In skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat. Brown the beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add the remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes on low heat.
Serve on buns.
Serves 6.

title: southern baked grits
directions: Stir grits into boiling water and cook according to box directions, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add butter. Stir well, then add grated cheese, savory salt, salt and a few drops of Tabasco sauce.
Fold in well-beaten eggs.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour crushed pineapple in bottom of cake pan (ungreased). Pour cherry Comstock over pineapple.
Pour yellow cake mix (dry) over top.
Melt 1 stick butter; pour on top.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix together soup, sour cream, cheese, salt, onion, green pepper and potatoes.
In baking dish, put 1/2 stick melted margarine, then pour in potato and soup mixture.
Top with corn flakes.
Pour 1/2 stick melted margarine on top of corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: banana split pie
directions: Spread over fruits and top with chopped pecans and cherries.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding milk last, until smooth.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven back to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.
Pie is done when knife comes out clean.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes and onion.
Peel garlic and chop.
Remove stem and seeds from chili and chop.
Place tomatoes, onion, garlic, chili and cilantro in blender or food processor container.
Blend or chop until desired consistency is reached.
Place mixture in bowl and add lime juice, sugar and chili powder.
Stir until well blended.
Serve with tortilla chips, wedges of baked fresh tortillas, as a sauce for cold or hot foods, as a topping for baked potatoes, or as a dressing for salad.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Add tomato sauce, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes, then uncover and cook until thick.
Chill in refrigerator until serving.

title: glorified grahams
directions: Cook butter, margarine and sugar until creamy, approximately 5 minutes. Pour over graham crackers and sprinkle with nuts. Bake 350° for 10 minutes. Cool on rack immediately, then break into chunks.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix the crushed pretzels, 4 tablespoons of sugar and melted margarine. Put it in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°. Cream together 1 cup sugar and cream cheese. Fold in Cool Whip which has been thawed.
Spread over cooled pretzels layer.

title: "candy"
directions: Melt chocolate in 200° oven with other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill to set.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl, folding together until blended.
Spoon into decorative serving bowl.
Chill.

title: cheese cake
directions: Butter and flour 9-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Cream the cheese. Add 1 egg at a time; beat after each egg until lemon color; add sugar and almond extract.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Let cool on rack for 15 minutes.

title: tuna bake
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Stir in tuna.
In another bowl, combine stuffing and butter.
In a casserole, alternate layers of macaroni and sauce.
Sprinkle topping over all.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Heat the first 3 ingredients just until melted and pour over cereal.
When cool, shake (in brown paper bag) in powdered sugar.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll bread dough out flat into a large rectangle 26 x 12-inch. Layer ham, cheese, cheese and pepperoni onto dough.
Roll up. Squeeze edges together and cut in half.
Squeeze inside edges also. Please on greased cookie sheet for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.
Bake at 375° or so.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and cook well.
Add milk, stirring gently to make a very heavy cream sauce.
Add seasoning and drained tuna.
Chill overnight.
Make into croquettes (cylinder shape) and roll in corn flake crumbs.
Bake in a 325° oven until bubbly.
Makes 10.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook
sliced
potatoes.
When
done, pour off water and use mixer
to
blend.
Add sugar, eggs, salt, vinegar, mayonnaise
and mustard.
Then add chopped onions, pickles, celery, peppers and whatever else you think will improve the taste.
A dash of this and that.

title: cranberry upside-down muffins
directions: Cut cranberries into halves; divide evenly into 12 greased muffin pans.
Spoon about 1 teaspoon of the butter into each. Sprinkle evenly with brown sugar.
In a mixing bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder, granulated sugar, salt and raisins.
In a smaller bowl, beat egg.
Mix in milk and remaining butter.
Add liquid mixture to flour mix.
Stir until moistened.
Spoon batter into cranberries.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 30 minutes. Let muffins cool for a few minutes and carefully take out.
Serve upside-down.

title: vegetable-tortellini soup
directions: Combine water, bouillon granules, basil and oregano and bring to boiling.
Stir in carrots and tortellini.
Return to boiling. Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and zucchini.
Return to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 3 to 5 minutes more or until vegetables and tortellini are tender. Stir in parsley. Makes 4 servings.

title: mocha chip melt-a-ways
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour and baking soda; set aside.
Beat together butter and sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets about 2 inches apart. Bake for 13 minutes or until light brown.
Cool on rack.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water slowly while making batter for cookies. Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Drain raisins, stir in 1 teaspoon baking soda; stir raisin mixture into batter.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bake and glaze teri ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving pieces; place meaty side up, in a shallow foil-lined baking pan.
Sprinkle garlic powder and pepper evenly over ribs.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit delight
directions: Note:
Delicious as a salad or dessert.

title: company style meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pack into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Simmer until done.
Add chopped onion and salt.
Add chili to tomato soup; simmer while stirring. Mixture should be consistency of gravy.
If dry, add small amount of water.
Line large casserole with 1/2 of the corn chips.
Pour in the meat mixture and add remaining chips on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and catsup.
Bake in 400° oven until cheese is melted. Serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan; flour, margarine and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Mix well cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread over first layer.
Mix together chocolate and vanilla pudding and milk.
Spread over second layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: caraway puffs
directions: In bowl, combine yeast, flour and baking soda.
Heat together cottage cheese, water, sugar, butter and salt.
Add egg, 2 teaspoons caraway seed and onion.
Add this mixture to dry mixture at high speed.
Stir in 1 cup more flour.
Place in greased bowl, turning once.
Cover; let rise until doubled (about 1 1/2 hours). Divide among 12 well-greased muffin pans.
Cover; let rise about 40 minutes.
When fingers are pressed lightly into dough and dents remain, dough is ready.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: angel cups
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in small balls; dip in sugar and flatten with glass.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy dill slaw
directions: Stir together first 8 ingredients in a large bowl until mixture is blended. Stir in coleslaw mix and cabbage. Cover and chill 8 hours. Garnish, if desired. Yield: 8 servings.

title: pineapple crunch cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using drained pineapple juice in place of water (water may have to be added to equal amount of liquid needed).
Pour 1/2 of the cake batter in 9 x 13-inch prepared pan.
Top with pineapple.
Pour remaining cake batter over pineapple.

title: pasta bolognese(kids in the kitchen)
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet. Add onion, carrots and celery. Saute over low-medium heat, stirring frequently, about 10 minutes. Stir in garlic. Saute 2 minutes more.
Add tomato sauce to skillet. Add basil and oregano. Stir.
Cook, covered, on medium-low heat for about 10 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mash and place 1/2 of chips in bottom of pan.
Brown hamburger; add taco seasoning and cumin to hamburger.
Place hamburger over chips.
Mix all soups and tomatoes together.
Then pour over hamburger.
Add cheese and remainder of chips on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: m 85's
directions: Combine lemon pepper, dill weed, garlic salt and dressing. Mix well.
Place crackers in a double brown paper bag.
Sprinkle mixture over crackers.
Pour oil over all.
Shake well.
Serve in bowl.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom of 11 x 9 cake pan. Mix pecans and coconut and spread on bottom of pan. Prepare mix as directed on box and pour over pecan and coconut mixture. Mix remaining ingredients and spoon over batter. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh strawberry dip
directions: Mix marshmallow cream and cream cheese together.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix together in double boiler.
Cook until a little thickened. If too thick after cooling, thin out with evaporated milk.

title: salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite-sized pieces into salad bowl. Alternate layers of egg and onion.
Make dressing of remaining ingredients.
Pour over lettuce.
Toss lightly.

title: all american franks and beans
directions: Saute onions; add remaining ingredients.
Heat up for 20 minutes.
Have a ball!

title: noodle pudding
directions: Use firm ripe apples.
Core apples, peel and slice.
Measure apples; add equal amount of cider.
Simmer apples until soft. Press through sieve, measure and add 1/2 as much sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Boil, stirring frequently, until thick.
Pour into Mason jars and fasten covers at once. If desired, add cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: teddye's rich biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Form biscuits on a greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crab cakes
directions: Gently mix all ingredients and shape into 8 large crab cakes. Fry cakes in oil for 5 minutes on each side or until brown. Serves 4.

title: cashew surprises
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Add nuts and noodles; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Makes approximately 100 candies.

title: pot roast
directions: Heat frying pan.
Add meat and brown on all sides.
Season with salt and pepper. Put onion slices on top of meat; add water. Cover and cook over low heat about 4 1/4 hours.
until meat is tender.
If desired, add peeled, halved potatoes, small peeled whole onions and carrots cut diagonally in 2-inch pieces during last hour of cooking.
Make gravy.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Boil celery and onions until tender; drain.
Add milk, sage, salt, pepper and margarine.
Then add bread pieces.
Pour on enough broth to moisten; mix well.
Set aside.

title: brenda's potato salad
directions: Cook the potatoes whole.
Peel and dice into a large bowl. While potatoes are cooking, boil the eggs.
Dice boiled eggs.
Add to potatoes with onion, sweet relish, pickle cubes, mustard and Miracle Whip.
Blend for consistency.
Refrigerate.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, celery and onion in a large pot. Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and allow vegetables to cook just until tender.
Add milk, butter and seasonings.
Simmer until hot.

title: low-fat mint brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) with cooking spray.
Mix ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake 30 minutes; cool.
