Cut into squares. Serves 32.

title: my best peanut brittle
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add the white sugar and syrup.
Boil till it will spin a thread when tested with a spoon.
Add 2 cups raw peanuts and pinch of salt.
Add peanuts and cook slowly over low heat till a golden brown.
Cook to 300°.
Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoon butter.
Add 2 teaspoons baking soda, 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Quickly stir and pour out on buttered cookie sheet, spreading it as thin as you can.

title: taco cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into ball.
Roll in paprika.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Add chopped eggs.
Fry bacon and onion until a delicate brown.
Strain, reserving bacon fat.
Add fat slowly to beaten egg and beat well.
Add vinegar and salt and pour over potatoes.
Mix lightly to blend well; heat in double boiler.
Serve hot.

title: linguini salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Marinate overnight.

title: pinto beans
directions: Prepare 1 to 2 cups of pinto beans as normal for cooking. Near end of cooking, add hot peppers, onion and sugar.
It's wonderful.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into pie crust.
Bake 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecan halves.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway comes out clean. Cool.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue hot dogs crock-pot style
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Cut up hot dogs into bite-size pieces. Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Pour into crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and blend well.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 15 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken salad sandwiches
directions: In a small bowl, combine chicken, celery, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and pepper.
Arrange lettuce leaves and tomato slices on 4 bread slices. Top with chicken mixture and remaining bread slices.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix egg yolks with milk.
Add cooked and drained spinach, cracker crumbs, onion, garlic salt, pepper and half of the butter. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly fold into spinach mixture. Place rest of butter in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add spinach mixture.
Cook in the oven in a pan of water at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: brittany's shortbread
directions: Mix oleo and sugar together, then mix in the flour.
Roll out about 1/2 inch thick and cut into shapes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
You can also use icing on them.
Good for any holiday.

title: turkey salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions and chill.
Stir in turkey, vegetables and dressing.
Makes 6 servings.
Serving size:
2 (No. 12) scoops (9.5 ounces), 210 calories, 17 protein, 32 cholesterol, 1 fat and 426 sodium.

title: raspberry fluff
directions: Tear cake into small pieces.
Set aside.
Beat whipping cream until it forms stiff peaks.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, combine cake and raspberries and fold in whipping cream. Spoon into dessert cups.

title: beef cubes in wine sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Pour into a medium sized crock-pot and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: lasagne
directions: Saute onion and pepper in olive oil.
Add ground round and brown.
Mash garlic with a small pinch of salt.
Add to meat.
Add water, tomato paste, Italian seasoning, chili powder, pepper and salt.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
While sauce cooks, prepare noodles.
Leave them in water.

title: fruit bowl supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill about 1 hour. Serve as dessert or as salad on crisped salad greens.
(Makes 6 cups or 12 servings.)

title: betty's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Stir in next 4 ingredients; spoon into a lightly oiled (Pam) 8-cup mold. Chill until firm and unmold on lettuce leaves.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Break or cut 1 loaf into small balls or pieces. Place in well-greased 9 x 13 pan. Melt margarine. Turn off heat. Add rest of ingredients; mix well and pour over bread. Add second loaf in small balls. Let rise midway up pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven. Turn upside down on larger sheet (to catch caramel syrup).

title: light and easy chocolate pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cocoa, sugar and butter.
Beat well.
Add flour, egg yolks and pecans.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites to soft peak stage and fold into chocolate mixture.
Add cinnamon.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 12 squares, cool and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice (with seasoned salt, if desired).
Drain well and cool to room temperature.
Place in a large bowl.
Add chicken, grapes, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Toss gently with a fork. Cover and chill.
Just before serving, add cashews, if desired. Serve on lettuce leaves or line bowl with lettuce leaves.
Yields 6 servings.

title: toothpick appetizers
directions: Arrange any combination of meat and cheese on a fringed toothpick.
Use pickle chunk or small olive to hold on at tip.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Melt marshmallows, sugar and milk together.
Add oleo, chocolate morsels and vanilla.
Boil one minute.
Stir well until chocolate is melted.
Place coconut over baked cake and pour over the chocolate mixture.
Chill until chocolate hardens.

title: raw apple bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add slightly beaten eggs, apples, milk, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Do not overmix.
Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan in moderate oven for about 25 minutes or until done.

title: easy manwich
directions: Brown meat; drain grease.
Add all ingredients and simmer until onion and pepper are tender.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.

title: easy breakfast quiche
directions: Spray 8 x 8-inch pan with Pam.
Layer green chiles, tomato, shredded cheese and fried bacon in pan.
Beat eggs, milk, Bisquick and salt together and pour over layered mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375° until golden brown.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water/wine and flour until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve over noodles or with crunchy French bread.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Peel and dice potatoes bite-size.
Cook until soft.
Fry bacon. Dump grease.
Cut into small pieces.
In large pot, put potatoes, bacon, corn and Carnation milk (enough to cover potatoes).
Add butter; salt to taste.
Heat on low to medium heat, stirring bottom to keep from burning.
Heat until corn is cooked.

title: spicy vegetable beef soup
directions: Combine beef and garlic in a Dutch oven; cook over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain meat in a colander and pat dry with a paper towel.
Wipe pan drippings from skillet with a paper towel.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add milk and corn and beat.
Bake at 350° until custard-like.

title: black raspberry ice cream dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and wine. Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened, then stir.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Chill about 1 hour.
Makes 7 servings.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Layer all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 8 x 13-inch pan.

title: spicy italian pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in flat casserole.
Cut onion in thin rings and place on top of pork chops.
Mix soup, oregano and Tabasco and spread over chops.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and artichoke hearts
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt, pepper and paprika; set aside.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Brown chicken pieces in butter.
Transfer chicken pieces to roasting pan.
Tuck artichoke hearts in between chicken pieces; set aside.
Add mushrooms to skillet; cook until golden.
Add broth, wine and rosemary.
Cook, stirring for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over chicken and artichoke hearts.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes until chicken is cooked.

title: school cookies
directions: In one big bowl mix flour, sugar and the vanilla.
Before you begin, melt the butter in a sauce pot.
Then begin to mix the ingredients.
Then pour the butter into a bowl.
Mix with hand; make balls and roll in hands.
Put on a non-greased cookie sheet. Press with 3 fingers and you're done.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or gold-brown on edges.

title: rabbit hot pot
directions: Cut meat in chunks.
Mix flour with salt and pepper and roll meat in it, then brown in the shortening.
Add garlic, tomatoes, onions, peppers and rosemary.
Add water, if necessary, to bring liquid halfway up the meat.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours, or until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Stir together whole-wheat flour in medium bowl. Separate small bowl. Dissolve yeast in warm water (105° to 115°). In large mixing bowl, combine milk, oil, honey and salt. Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast mixture, eggs and 1/4 of the flour mixture. Beat well with electric mixer. Add remaining flour in stages. Beat by hand after each addition. When dough gets too stiff to mix, knead by hand on clean, lightly floured work surface until smooth. Place in lightly greased bowl and cover with dish towel. Set in a warm place. Let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour. Press the air out again and form into small fist sized rolls. Place on a greased baking sheet. While rising a second time, preheat oven to 350°. After doubled in size, roll dough into small balls and place in groups of 3 into well buttered muffin pan. Bake for 12 minutes until golden brown. Makes 24.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for 45 minutes.
Mix all together very well.
Put mixture into 10-inch greased pie pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with the milk.
Roll nuts, orange slices, and dates in the flour.
Add along with coconut to batter.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan, 275° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: snowballs
directions: Beat all ingredients except nuts.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Roll into balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
When warm, roll in 10x sugar.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir onion in margarine in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Stir in shrimp.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil
chicken until tender. Debone and break into pieces. Mix with other ingredients. Bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and next three ingredients together, then drain. Add rest of ingredients and simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough into half and roll out on dough sheet.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aunt carol's beef and noodles
directions: Brown roast well.
Add enough water to make broth for noodles. Mix eggs, flour and salt.
Add water to mix if needed.
Turn out onto heavily floured surface.
Roll out thin, let dry and cut into noodles.
Drop into boiling broth after removing roast.
Cook until done.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: margie's vegetable soup
directions: Add all raw vegetables to stew pot and cook for 30 minutes. Add salt, butter, tomatoes, tomato soup, fill pot 3/4 full with water stirring occasionally to keep stew from sticking.
Stew is ready to serve and can be served with crackers or over corn bread with a glass of ice cold tea.

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onions together.
Drain the fat off meat.
Add the chili seasoning, tomatoes, tomato paste, chili beans and brown sugar.
Add enough water to make it the right consistency.
Cook for about 30 minutes on low heat and stir to make sure it doesn't stick.
Great on cold winter days.

title: dirty rice
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, adding 1 can water.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: country-style cole slaw
directions: In medium bowl, stir together the first 6 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well. Cover; chill at least 2 hours. Makes 4 cups.

title: open-faced grilled cheese and tomato
directions: Toast bread.
Add the cheese and tomato.
Sprinkle oregano on top, then add the bacon.
Place in a 350° oven under the broiler until lightly browned.

title: chef's salt(this is a must for every cook)
directions: Mix all ingredients well and keep in jar.
Use instead of salt for steaks, roasts, stews, burgers and meat loaf.
This recipe is from the Bakery in Chicago.

title: golden mushrooms
directions: Cut stems from mushrooms; finely chop enough stems to measure 1/2 cup.
Mix chopped stems, onions, celery and margarine in 1-quart casserole.
Cook, uncovered, on High until onion is tender (2 to 3 minutes).
Stir in bread crumbs, lemon pepper, marjoram and turmeric.

title: lemon jello pound cake
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup hot water and cool.
Add to cake mix and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Add oil and lemon extract and beat.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together 2 sticks soft butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift all-purpose flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to batter with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add flavoring.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cake delight
directions: Prepare cake by package directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.
While cake bakes, mix pineapple and sugar. Heat until dissolves.
Make vanilla pudding by directions until thickens.
Remove cake from oven.
Punch holes in cake surface with toothpick.
Spoon pineapple mixture over cake.
Spoon vanilla pudding over cake.
Chill cake in refrigerator.
Spread whipped topping on top and sprinkle with coconut and chopped pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Then add sifted dry ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Cover bottom of glass with cloth and moisten.
Dip in sugar.
Press balls flat.
Makes 6 dozen.
Bake at 325°.

title: cajun chinese rice
directions: Rice should be cooked, but not mushy.
Let cool.
Cut meat into strips 1/2 inch wide and 1 inch long.
You may also use chicken cubes if you would like.
Fry meat until tender; pour off grease. Add bell pepper, cut in half and sliced.
Stir-fry until tender but not mushy.
Add to rice.
Stir in Kitchen Bouquet and soy sauce until color is brown.
Add Cajun seasoning and garlic powder to taste.
Serve in large servings.
Caution:
easily addicted to.

title: gazpacho
directions: Put 1 cup broth into a blender with all the vegetables.
Work into a thick puree.
Add the remaining cup of broth, lemon juice and olive oil and salt to taste.
Let stand and chill at least 3 hours so flavors blend well.
Serve cold, garnished with Bac*Os, croutons and/or tomato and cucumber cubes.
Good with a second course of beans and rice, or as lunch with a sandwich.

title: sunday breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain; set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, put the buttered bread cubes, top with the sausage, then cheese.
Beat the eggs, add milk, dry mustard and salt.
Mix well and pour over the sausage mixture.
Can be made the night before.
Keep in icebox, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese danish
directions: Place one can of rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan, sealing perforations.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and egg yolk.
Cream together.
Spread over rolls.
Place second tube of rolls on top, sealing perforations.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes in pan.
Brush with egg white and water; sprinkle almonds on top.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Fritos.
Add Fritos before serving and mix.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 to 10 minutes in very little water; drain and cool.
Mix all other together.
Put broccoli and mixture into large buttered casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top and dot with butter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except muffin mix.
Stir in muffin mix last.
Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: macaroni and cheese supper salad
directions: Drain and rinse salmon or tuna.
Prepare macaroni dinner and add remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill.
Add frozen peas, chunks of cheese and celery.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar,	eggs,
food
coloring and cocoa together well.
Sift together
flour,
baking
soda
and salt. Fold in buttermilk, vinegar
and
vanilla.	Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool cake for 10 minutes in pan, then remove and cool completely.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine the sugars and milk in a heavy pot.
Cook slowly over a low flame until it reaches 238 degrees on a candy thermometer. Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla, and pecans.
Beat mixture with a wooden spoon until it is smooth and creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: remi's pigs in blanket
directions: Separate biscuits into layers.
Roll each layer flat.
Fold cocktail wiener and roll.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Place in oven at 350° to 400° until browned.

title: honey pecan snack mix
directions: Combine Crispix cereal, pretzels and pecans in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Set aside.
In a large saucepan, combine margarine, sugar and honey; bring mixture to a boil and continue to boil for 5 minutes.
Do not stir. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: kids favorite fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix gently.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix 5 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and apples; set aside. Mix batter (remaining ingredients) and then layer batter, layer apples, etc. End with batter. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Works well in a tube or Bundt pan. "Grease pan."

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the soup and potato chips; mix well.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour soup on top without mixing it up.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: trash bag candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine.
Cook on low heat until melted.
Stir in Rice Chex until covered with chocolate mixture.
Pour into a clean trash bag.
Pour powdered sugar over top.
Shake until covered.
Store in airtight container.

title: virginia's hot chicken
directions: Dice onion and peppers into skillet with butter.
Cook until medium brown.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasoning.
Place pre-fried chicken in pan and pour sauce over chicken.
Cover.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour or in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours on high.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients first, then add in additional ingredients.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Alternating, add flour and milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in flavoring.

title: decadent fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Dissolve soda in buttermilk, stir well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with flour.
Add 1 cup mini-morsels, melted chocolate, chocolate syrup, and vanilla, stirring until blended.
Don't overbeat.
Spoon batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert cake immediately and let cool.

title: russian rice
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add noodles and brown.
Add the consomme and bring to a boil.
Add rice and boil again.
Put lid on pan and simmer on low for 45 minutes.
Do not lift lid.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch or three 3 x 6-inch pans.
Bake until top is golden brown and slightly split, 1 hour and 20 minutes for large loaf; small loaves about 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: mexican lunch(makes 4 to 5 servings)
directions: Brown sausage, onion and peppers in a large skillet.
Add tomatoes, buttermilk, macaroni and seasonings.
Cover; cook until steaming.
Lower heat to simmer and cook for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook hamburger and onion.
Pour off excess fat.
Add large can tomato sauce, garlic, green pepper and other seasonings.
Simmer approximately one hour.
Add small can tomato sauce and mushrooms. Simmer another hour or so.
(Tomato sauce is salty so salt to taste.)

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger; let drain in a colander.
Saute onions, green pepper and celery.
Add hamburger, tomato paste, water and tomatoes; mix well, chopping tomatoes up well.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
More water may be needed.
Stir well occasionally, to be sure it isn't sticking to the bottom of the pan.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and butter; beat in sugar.
Add eggs, flour, salt, and baking powder; beating well.
Mix in milk, vanilla and cocoa. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bananas & cheesecake dipping sauce
directions: Place all ingredients except bananas in blender and blend until smooth.
Pour 2 Tbsp Sauce into each of 6 plastic containers; cover tightly.
Refrigerate until needed or place containers in small cooler with ice.

title: raita salad(india)
directions: Peel, halve and seed the cucumbers; grate, using a food processor or hand grater.
Place in a medium bowl.
Add yogurt, mint and white pepper and stir to combine.
Cover the yogurt mixture and refrigerate it until needed.
To serve, arrange each sliced tomato on individual plates; top with the cucumber mixture. Serves 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cherries and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on dry cake mix.
Dot with small pieces of margarine.
Do not blend. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with Cool Whip.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out or pat on a floured surface to 1-inch thickness.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes about 16 biscuits.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas and cheese together, stirring well.
Place 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center of each flour tortilla and roll.
Place seam side down in greased baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Put potatoes and onion into a 3-quart saucepan and barely cover with cold water. Add salt. Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Mash potatoes in their liquid. Add butter, evaporated milk and water. Stir and add a little more water if soup is too thick. Reheat to scalding. Remove from heat. Stir in chopped parsley. Serves 5.

title: cowboy supper
directions: Place half of sliced potatoes in bottom of baking dish.
Put half of chili and beans on top of potatoes.
Add half of the ground beef.
Repeat these layers.
On top, add sliced onions and desired amount of catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 45 minutes.

title: sour cream gingerbread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until done.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Use mixer; mix all ingredients together except ham; spread onto ham slices.
Roll ham up and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight. Cut into 4 or 5 pieces.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve. Makes 50 to 75 bite size pieces.

title: chocolate or butterscotch delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar and spread over cooled crust, then chill.
Mix the instant pudding, milk and vanilla.
Spread over the cream cheese layer.
Cover all with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: mulligan(this is zada porter's recipe)
directions: Cook and
debone
meat.
Cook
potatoes, onions and rice separately; drain off
water
and add meat and broth.
Add just enough broth to cover all of this.
Add other ingredients as it cooks.
Keep well stirred to keep from scorching.

title: creamy chocolate frosting(makes your cupcakes look store bought)
directions: Combine butter, cocoa and milk in a small saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until butter melts.
Remove from heat and add salt and vanilla.
Gradually add powdered sugar a cup at a time, beating at high speed on an electric mixer until thick enough to spread, adding additional milk if necessary.
I use this for my cupcakes because you can swirl them and they look perfect. If it starts getting a little hard to swirl, heat on low heat.

title: bucko's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together, shape into a loaf and place in baking dish or pan.
Put some catsup on top of the loaf.
Bake one hour or until done.

title: moravian sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and extract together.
Add sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and baking soda together.
Add in fourths to creamed mixture, mixing until blended.
Chill dough overnight using a small amount of dough at a time; roll out dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch rounds and press pecan piece onto center.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 7 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix package of cream cheese and sour cream until a spreadable consistency.
Spread mixture over large plate or serving dish. Next, spread chili from can on top of this.
Top with shredded cheese.
I place in microwave and heat until cheese is all melted. All done.
Serve with your favorite chips.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine sugar, baking soda, salt and buttermilk in Dutch oven. Cook over high heat to 210° on candy thermometer (about 5 minutes).
Stir frequently, scraping sides and bottom of pan.
Add butter and pecans.
Cook, stirring constantly to very soft ball sate (230° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; cool 2 minutes.
Beat until thickened and creamy.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Makes 15 pralines.

title: caledonian cream
directions: Process cottage cheese, marmalade and confectioners sugar and mix in blender container until smooth.
Pan into 4 to 6 dessert dishes.
Chill well.
Garnish with candied fruit and almonds.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Melt butter and vegetable oil in a skillet over low heat. Combine flour and salt; coat chicken with mixture and fry over low heat until browned on one side; turn to brown on all sides evenly.
Add water.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, adding more water if necessary.
Uncover and cook for 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: ella's beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese and fruit strudel
directions: Place pastry sheet on parchment-lined cookie sheet.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread entire mixture over 1/2 of pastry sheet.
Spread fruit over cream cheese.
Cut 8 vent holes in other half of pastry sheet.
Fold pastry sheet over and crimp edges with a fork to seal.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: my favorite cheese ball
directions: Combine onions, 3/4 cup pecans and salt.
Using a mixer, mix cream cheese with onion, nuts and salt.
Chill in same bowl.
When chilled, about 1 hour, shape mixture into a ball and roll in 1/2 to 3/4 cup chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whole wheat crackers.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine condiments and mix well.
Add salmon and bread crumbs. Bake in a greased 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Garnish with curly endive, lemon and cucumber twist, if desired.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream the butter and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Sift the flour and cornstarch together and cut into butter mixture until coarse meal.
Knead 1 to 2 minutes until smooth and press into cookie sheet.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until pale brown.
Do not overbake.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: brownie mocha pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa and sprinkle over top.
Pour 1 3/4 cups hot water over entire batter.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or so.
Wonderful warm with vanilla ice cream on top.

title: fabulous carrot cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, crushed pineapple and juice, oil, vanilla, salt, coconut, carrots and pecans.
Add dry ingredients.

title: diced baked potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in baking pan.
Sprinkle with seasonings; dot with butter.
Quarter onion and place between potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour into large skillet or Bundt pan which has been well greased with Crisco.
Bake at 300° until done (approximately 45 minutes).

title: low fat bread pudding
directions: Tear or crumble bread and set aside.
In large bowl, combine egg substitute, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla, evaporated milk, raisins, Molly McButter and cranberry sauce.
Mix well and stir in the bread.

title: ranch potato crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash potatoes and leave skin on.
With a garnisher, slice potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place sliced potatoes, approximately 4 cups into a bowl with a fitted lid.
Add vegetable oil; stir to coat.
Add salad dressing mix.
Cover bowl with lid and shake until potatoes are coated.
Line potato slices in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Do not overlap slices.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are brown.
Serve warm. Yields approximately 40 potato crisps.

title: fried white potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and onions.
Slice.
Heat oil in iron skillet until hot.
Season potatoes with salt and pepper.
Drop in hot grease.
Let cook on low heat until tender.
Add onions.
Cover and cook until onions are tender.
Sprinkle flour over onions and potatoes.
Cook until brown.
Add water.
Cover.
Open and stir until it makes a smooth gravy.
Serve with steak or lean meat and hot biscuit.

title: hearty lentil soup
directions: Place the ingredients in a slow cooker except the cabbage. Stew for 8 to 9 hours on low setting.
Remove bones and cut meat into soup.
Turn the slow cooker to high and add the cabbage. Cook 30 to 40 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.
Freezes well.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make at least 4 hours ahead or the day before.

title: sesame-vegetable lo mein
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions. Heat 2 Tbsp oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat 1 minute or until hot. Add peas and next 7 ingredients, and stir-fry 5 to 7 minutes or until crisp and tender.

title: bacon-beef-chicken bake
directions: Line bottom of a baking dish with beef.
Wrap each breast with a strip of bacon and place each one on a slice of beef.
Mix soup and sour cream until smooth.
Pepper breasts.
Pour soup mixture over breasts.
Cook, uncovered, at 250° for 3 hours (can rush at a higher temperature).

title: garlic bread
directions: Slice bread lengthwise.
Spread with margarine; sprinkle with garlic powder.
Put loaf back together; slice crosswise into rounds.
Wrap bread in foil.
Warm in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until hot.

title: amish cabbage salad
directions: In a large bowl combine first three ingredients.
In a small bowl combine rest of ingredients to make dressing.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Toss until well coated.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: cheesy-chicken ball
directions: Drain chicken and mix well with cream cheese.
Add mayo, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Roll in pecans. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Can be made weeks in advance and frozen.
Delicious!

title: taco soup
directions: Cook hamburger and onion (drain fat).
Add all remaining ingredients (including liquid from the cans).
Simmer until thick.

title: microwave apples
directions: Put apples in a microwave-safe dish.
Place pats of margarine on top and finish with the spices.
Cook on high for 15 to 20 minutes.
Time varies.
Sweeten with sugar or sugar substitute.

title: colossal cornbread
directions: Add sugar, shortening and salt to milk.
Add yeast to warm water.
Add yeast and eggs to milk when cool.
Add meal and flour. Mix and knead until smooth.
Oil lightly, cover and put in warm place to double in bulk.
Knead again.
Shape into loaves, about 3.
Let double in bulk again.
Cook at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and mix with cheese, mayonnaise, water chestnuts (drained) and onions.
Put in casserole dish.
Crush crackers and pour melted butter over top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shepard pie
directions: Peel and cook potatoes, mash and set aside.
Cook and drain hamburger put in dish with soup.
Add drained corn and top with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are light brown.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Add all ingredients except egg whites.
Mix well.
Last fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in buttered baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle top with paprika if desired.

title: chocolate or lemon delight
directions: Mix and pat flour and margarine in a 9 x 13-inch dish pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of nuts over crust.
Bake at 350° until light brown, then cool.

title: low-fat pie crust
directions: Mix half of oil with dry ingredients until it resembles cornmeal.
Add rest of oil and mix until size of peas.
Add vinegar and milk and mix into dough.
Roll out between two pieces of waxed paper.
Makes two pie shells.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: quick pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients slowly, reserving 1/2 of whipped topping for pie topping.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, water and applesauce.
Sift together all dry ingredients, then add raisins, cloves and nuts.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: della davis' sweet potato pie
directions: Combine potatoes, butter and sugar.
Beat yolks.
Add to potato mixture.
Add flavoring and spices.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Fold into mixture.
Pour in unbaked crust.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until firm.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Pour washed, drained berries into unbaked pie shell.
Mix sugar, tapioca, flour and cinnamon.
Spread evenly over berries and dot with butter.
Put top crust on pie.
Make some slits in top and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Mix raisins with boiling water.
Stir and set aside.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and pork and beans until beans are broken.
Add flour and rest of dry ingredients to bean mixture.
Add 1 cup nuts and vanilla.
Drain raisins and add, stirring to mix well.
Pour batter into 3 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake in 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients; let cool and then add remaining ingredients.
Let
set
for a couple of hours or overnight for best flavor.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch. Add vinegar and water. Boil 5 minutes. Add beets and let stand over low heat 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter at low speed.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, little at a time.
Add flavoring; bake 1 hour at 350° in tube pan, greased and floured.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 15 minutes longer.
Do not open oven during the entire baking time.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles, uncovered, in boiling water 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Combine soup, milk, water and Cheddar cheese in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese melts and sauce is hot.
Stir in cooked noodles, turkey, peas, carrots and pimiento.
Spoon mixture into greased 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: butter fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Mix in flour and nutmeg.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
This may be cooked in large tube pan or two large loaf pans.
For tube pan, bake at 200° for 5 hours.
For loaf pans, cook at 200° for 3 hours.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In large skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in beans, soup, water, salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1 can of biscuits.
Bake in a 350° oven until biscuits are done.

title: stuffed bakers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut potatoes lengthwise.
Put pats of butter on.
Cut onions in quarters. Put 2 1/4 slices on top of butter.
Salt and pepper oregano to taste.
Wrap in tinfoil. Place on cookie sheet and bake approximately 1 hour.

title: lemon meringue cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a 10-inch tube pan.
Cool. Split into 3 layers.
Stir pudding until smooth.
Spread 1/3 of filling between each and layer on top.
Frost sides and center with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Light and delicious.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 cup nuts.
Form ball.
(I put this in the freezer for a few minutes so that it will be easier to put in the shape of a ball.)
Roll the ball in the remaining nuts.

title: beef and bean tostados
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix and water.
Stir; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until liquid is reduced.

title: lite mushroom frittata
directions: In medium bowl, combine Egg Beaters, cheese, milk, garlic powder with parsley and seasoned pepper; set aside.
Spray a 10-inch ovenproof nonstick skillet lightly with vegetable oil cooking spray.
Over medium-high heat, cook zucchini, tomato and mushrooms for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add egg mixture, stirring well. Cover; cook over low heat for 15 minutes or until almost set. Remove lid and place skillet under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes or until desired tenderness.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pheasant with grapes and white wine sauce
directions: Cut pheasant into parts and smear with crushed garlic cloves. Melt butter in Dutch oven and saute pheasant all over until golden brown.
Remove bird.
Add flour, stock, wine and lemon juice; blend smoothly and bring to a boil.
Season to taste.

title: strawberry (raspberry) cake
directions: Beat all together for 4 to 5 minutes with electric mixer. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost.

title: vanilla cream
directions: Pour Pepsi into a tall glass; add ice.
Add 2 tablespoons milk or cream.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Stir until well mixed. Tastes like an ice cream float but without the ice cream.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 2 hours.
Roll in small balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 70 balls.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add margarine, egg and milk; mix well.
Bake in muffin pan in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add water to thin; cook down. Makes 2 servings.

title: cabbage biscuits
directions: Cook cabbage, onion and hamburger until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Set this aside.

title: parmesan knots
directions: Tie each biscuit piece into a knot and bake as package directs. As soon as out of the oven, put into a mixture of the remainder of ingredients.
Absorb as much mixture as possible.
Put in pan and pour rest of mixture over knots.
Freeze.
Reheat at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and orange juice separately, then pour all into punch bowl.
Mix well.

title: granola
directions: Mix ingredients together. Spread mixture on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325 for 20-25 minutes. Add 1/2 Cup of raisins. Cool & Enjoy!

title: carrot pudding
directions: In a saucepan, heat carrots that have been pared and shredded in the 1 1/2 cups water to boiling; reduce heat and simmer until water is absorbed (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Stir in milk, cream and sugar; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-high.
Cook until liquid is absorbed (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients; simmer until mixture is very thick.
Serve warm.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add onion, then add spaghetti mix and tomato sauce.
Simmer a few minutes, then put into a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 square pans.
Add mushrooms and peppers (optional). Cover with cheese.
Unroll rolls and put over cheese.
Spread over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: "slumber party french toast"
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon, stir and then set aside.
Combine eggs and milk in a shallow bowl.
Dip bread slices into egg mixture to coat both sides.
Lay slices over sugar-cinnamon mixture in baking pan.
Pour any remaining egg mixture over the bread slices.
Cover pan with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Remove pan from fridge 1 hour before baking to reach room temperature.
Preheat oven to 375°. Bake 25 minutes with foil on.
Remove foil and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients and
press into bottom of 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mock ravioli casserole
directions: Combine tomato juices.
Season and heat.
Chop onions and saute in butter.
Brown ground meat and drain off fat.
Add meat and onions to sauce.
Simmer for 40 minutes.

title: biscuit squares
directions: Measure biscuit mix into large bowl. In small bowl, stir together sour cream and milk; stir into biscuit mix to form a soft dough. Turn out onto surface dusted with additional biscuit mix; knead 10 times. Shape into an 8 x 8 inch square pan.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook salad macaroni until tender, drain and rinse.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with mixture of chips and butter.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a Dutch oven (or heavy pan, covered) and cook 5 hours in oven at 250°.

title: lemon herb marinated chicken
directions: In cup, mix the first 5 ingredients.
Pour over chicken. Cover and let stand at room temperature no longer than 30 minutes, turning once.
Broil 10 minutes or until thoroughly cooked, turning once.
Serves 4.

title: lemon freeze
directions: Line 9 x 9-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Whip well chilled evaporated milk until thick.
Add sugar, lemon juice, lemon extract and yellow food coloring.
Freeze.
Cut in squares to serve.
Garnish as desired.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Heat beans and add to beef.
Add chopped lettuce and tomatoes.
Add cheese.
Mix with Fritos and dressing when ready to serve.

title: speedy sausage and pasta
directions: Saute sausage, add pepper, onion, and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender.
Stir in tomatoes, mushrooms, olives, salt, paprika and pepper flakes.
Bring to a boil.
reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Cook pasta and combine with sausage mix.

title: spicy low fat low calorie spinach dip
directions: Heat oil in a non-stick skillet over medium high heat and add onions and garlic.
Cook about 3 minutes and transfer to food processor or food chopper.
Add remaining ingredients, except water chestnuts, and process until almost smooth.
Scrape into a serving bowl and stir in water chestnuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill until serving time.

title: parmesan eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel eggplant and trim off the ends. Cut the eggplant into 6 to 8 slices, each about half an inch thick.
Blend the butter and cheese and spread the eggplant slices on both sides with the mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Arrange the slices on a baking sheet in one layer.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until tender throughout.
Serve sprinkled with chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: syrian cheese (joban)
directions: Heat milk until lukewarm.
Stir.
Press down on milk.
Let set. Drain liquid.
Make patties with hands.
Salt lightly each pattie of cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: pioneer stew
directions: Roll stew meat in flour. Heat oil in large cast-iron or enamel stew pot. Brown meat on medium heat.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.

title: corn custard casserole
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Stir in remainder of the ingredients.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: gourmet mustard
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar with the mustard, flour and salt.
Put this mixture into a 2-quart cooking pot.
Whisk in the evaporated milk and cook on a low setting.

title: banana smoothe(quick treat)
directions: Using a blender, whip ingredients until stiff.
Freeze for 10 minutes.

title: buttery cinnamon skillet apples
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in sugar and cornstarch; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover!
Cook over medium heat, spooning sauce over apples occasionally, until apples are fork-tender and sauce is thickened (12 to 15 minutes).
To serve, place 2 apple halves in individual dessert dishes; spoon 1/2 cup sauce over each half.
Yields 4 servings and 2 cups sauce.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Hollow out mushroom caps.
Saute stems and onion.
Stir in salami, cheese spread and catsup.
Stuff caps and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: coq au vin
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Add broth, wine, mushrooms, onions and seasonings.
Cover; cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf. Gradually blend water into flour until smooth.
Slowly stir into sauce.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange buttermilk cake
directions: Grate the orange rind.
Halve oranges, squeeze juice into saucepan.
Add one cup of sugar.
Add the grated rind to the butter.
Add remaining sugar.
Cream until soft and light, using medium speed on mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat until light. Beat in the baking soda, baking powder and flour alternating with the buttermilk.
Mix until smooth.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Turn into a lightly buttered 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Bring orange juice and sugar to a boil.
Pour the boiling syrup over the hot cake as it comes out of the oven.
Set cake aside to cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Beat in vanilla.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to shortening mixture, blending thoroughly.
Stir in M&M's candies.
Drop by teaspoons on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crunch top potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan in 375° oven. Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch slices crosswise. Place in single layer in pan. Turn once in margarine.

title: rocky road
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients and cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool completely and cut.

title: jambalaya
directions: Make roux.
Add flour to hot bacon drippings over medium heat, stirring continually, until flour is dark brown.
Do not burn! Add the Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, bell pepper, onions, scallions, parsley and garlic.
Cook until soft, stirring constantly.
Add water and rice; stir until comes to a boil. Cover; decrease to simmer until rice is cooked.
In a frying pan, saute sausage, chicken and ham in butter until cooked.
Add meat to cooked rice mixture.
Simmer for 2 hours, stirring and adding additional liquid (1 cup chicken bouillon) as needed.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: squash boats
directions: Boil squash whole until tender.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Cut squash in half longways and scoop out middle to make a boat; save the middle for use later.
Brown your ground round; drain fat. Add seasoning and water to consistency called for on French's pack.
Add the scooped out squash and let simmer for about 10 minutes.
Stuff squash "boats" with ground meat stuffing.
Place in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and continue cooking for approximately 5 minutes until cheese melts. Cool slightly, then serve.
Mmmmmm good!

title: ripe tomato catsup
directions: Boil down until thick.	Put into jars.	Seal.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Whip the topping and mix all ingredients together.
Put in pans or molds and freeze.
Serves 25.

title: dill rolls with mushroom soup
directions: Mix ground beef lightly with egg, bread crumbs, water, mustard and salt until well blended; divide into 8 equal portions (about 1/2 cup each).

title: chili
directions: Cook 30 minutes before adding beans and corn.
Then cook additional 30 minutes.
(Do as you usually do for chili.)

title: soup a l'oignon maison(onion soup)
directions: Melt butter and oil; add onion and stir.
Cover pan and cook on low heat 15 to 20 minutes until onions are tender.
Uncover, raise heat to medium-high; stir in salt and sugar.
Stir until sugar caramelizes.
Cook 30 minutes until onions are a dark brown.
Stir often.
Lower heat and stir in flour to make paste with onions. Cook slowly for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour 1 cup hot broth, stirring with wire whip to blend flour.
Add rest of broth and ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with French bread and Parmesan cheese.

title: egg noodles with sour cream
directions: Cook noodles.
Melt butter in a large pan.
Add chopped green onion, sour cream, cheese, nutmeg and noodles.
Toss lightly.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix shortening, egg, sugar and molasses.
Sift remaining ingredients together and add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Continue beating and add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Fold in nuts or raisins.
Spoon into two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown on top.
Cool on rack.
Serves 8.

title: fruit glow punch(all ingredients should be cold when mixed)
directions: Combine all liquids and mix well.
Add sherbet either in balls or chunks, serve immediately.
DO NOT ADD ICE TO THIS PUNCH. The chilled liquids and sherbet keep it cold.
Some people think this is alcoholic because of the apple juice.

title: layered pudding dessert
directions: Mix and pat flour, nuts and margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Beat until fluffy 1 cup of Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread on cooled crust.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Line an 8-inch pie plate with pastry.
Sift sugar and flour together and combine with beaten egg.
Stir rhubarb into mixture. Pour into pastry lined plate.
Cover with top crust or lattice crust.
Trim and seal.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° for about 35 minutes.

title: hawaiian surprise
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, pineapple, oranges and coconut. Sprinkle dry Jell-O over mixture and mix together.
Add no other liquid.
Add Cool Whip.
Chill.
Sprinkle with berries before serving.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown hamburg, onion
and
celery.
Add 3 gallons water and 1 gallon tomato puree; add seasonings.
Boil, thicken with cornstarch mixed with
water.
Add kidney beans.
Pressure can 1 hour at 10 pound pressure or cold pack 2 hours.

title: hot pepper surprise
directions: Fry hamburger and potatoes until almost done.
Add hot peppers.
Season to taste.
Drain fat.
Place back on stove and melt cheese on top.
Good served with fried biscuits.

title: leann's lemon squares
directions: Sift flour and powdered sugar into bowl.
Blend in butter with fingertips until well mixed.
Pat evenly into the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot honey topping
directions: Soak apricots at least one hour in hot water in covered dish. Put honey, apricots and half of soaking water in blender; puree. Add whipping cream and blend 20 seconds.
Chill.
Serve on your favorite cake.

title: chocolate peanut pillows
directions: Hershey bars may be substituted, 1 ounce each, but eliminate powdered sugar if bars are used.

title: nut paddies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers into a bowl.
Cover with cut-up tomatoes, alfalfa sprouts, 1 onion (diced) and then crumble feta cheese over top.
Cover with salad dressing prior to serving.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook butter and onion until transparent.
Add flour to butter mixture.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Mix in chicken broth.
Add milk.
Stir together.
Bring to boil.
Add Cheez Whiz and let melt.
May add cooked frozen vegetables.
May add water to thin. May add mustard for taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then add to broccoli.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Crush crackers on top; dot with butter. Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cocoa cinnamon strata bundt
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs and sour cream and beat five minutes.
Meanwhile in a small bowl combine nuts, sugar, cocoa and cinnamon.
Alternate, spooning layers of cake batter and topping into greased and floured two quart Bundt pan, beginning and ending with cake batter.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until cake tester inserted comes out clean. Let cool 10 minutes; turn out.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: dutch apple crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line pie pan with pastry.
Pare apples and slice thin.
Mix 1/2 cup of sugar, salt and desired spices. Pour over apples.
Toss lightly with a fork.
Put in unbaked shell. Combine remaining sugar and flour; add butter.
Rub together until crumbs are formed.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 40 minutes or until apples are thoroughly cooked.
Serve warm with Cheddar cheese.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies until fine.
Melt oleo and mix into crumbs. Press into an 8 x 12-inch glass dish.
Mix together cheese and sugar.
Add half of the Cool Whip.
Spread on top of crumb mixture. Mix pudding and remaining oleo together.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle top with a few cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: boston baked beans 1
directions: Sort and wash beans thoroughly.
Soak overnight in salted water to cover.
The following day, cook beans 30 minutes; drain.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add vanilla, dry ingredients and cinnamon.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave taco casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, pouring off excess fat, then add onion, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Then cook this mixture for 5 to 10 minutes in microwave oven.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour over chicken (approximately 4 to 6 pieces). Cover and refrigerate overnight or for 8 hours. Keep 1/2 cup of the sauce for marinating while cooking; toss the remaining sauce. Grill or bake until done.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Prepare roll mix according to directions on box.
Roll out on floured board and cut 6-inch circles.
Fill circles with pepperoni, cheese and olive mixture.
Work with hands and form a smooth ball with all mixture covered with dough.
Drop into hot oil and deep fry 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 20 servings.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown venison and beef in shortening in a large heavy pot, over moderate heat.
Add garlic and onions.
Cook until golden, stirring frequently.
Add water and tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover loosely and simmer for 3 hours.
Add seasonings and cook 1 hour or longer.
Serve at once or let stand, covered, overnight in refrigerator.
Reheat.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add chili powder, salt and pepper, mixing well.
Add tomato paste and water; mix well.
Add chili beans; mix and simmer for approximately 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal coffee cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water.
Add to other ingredients. Mixture is kind of runny.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3 tablespoons warm water.
Combine sugar, shortening, 1 cup warm water, salt and eggs in large bowl; mix well.
Add yeast and flour; beat until smooth.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: raspberry coconut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package for two 9-inch round cake layers, adding 2/3 cup of coconut to batter.

title: lasagne
directions: Add hamburger and minced garlic.
Brown.
Then add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles.
Put alternate layers of noodles, Mozzarella, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Parmesan cheese in greased pan. End with meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Serves 4.

title: chicken vollrath
directions: Boil and cube chicken.
Heat last 4 ingredients.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer 1/2 of spaghetti and all of chicken. Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Then layer 1/2 of sauce, rest of spaghetti, layer of Parmesan cheese, rest of sauce and layer of Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Put oil in bowl.
Stir in sugar, eggs, vanilla and apples. Sift dry ingredients and stir in nuts.
Combine flour mixture with oil mixture.
Stir.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Pour icing over hot cake.

title: dad's favorite sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together; pour into pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cool and easy pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix cold ice and juice to make 1 cup.
Stir until chilled and remove extra ice.
Stir in whipped topping with whisk; refrigerate until thick, 10 to 15 minutes.
Spoon into crust and serve when ready.
Serves 6.

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a jelly roll pan.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Pat dough in bottom and sides of pan.
Cook beef, onion, garlic and green pepper until beef is brown.
Mix tomato sauce and Italian seasoning.
Spread sauce over dough.
Spoon beef mixture over sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: cheddar pepper muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Generously grease 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, pepper and salt. In small bowl, combine milk, oil and egg until blended.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Fold in 3/4 cup of the cheese.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over tops.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let cool in pan or on wire rack 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve warm.

title: diet vegetable dip
directions: Blend all in blender until smooth.
Makes 2 cups basic dip.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Grind cranberries.
Dissolve strawberry Jell-O with 2 cups hot water.
Add pineapple juice in place of cold water.
Add sugar. Cut up apples into chunks.
Add to mix with walnuts.
Put into mold and refrigerate.

title: duck and sauerkraut
directions: Brown ducks in butter.
Add onion and saute.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Lift ducks on top sauerkraut. Cover and cook 20 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tofu spinach souffle
directions: Mix well and place in a shallow baking dish.
Top with Pimento "Cheese" Spread (see recipe).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Good cold also.

title: lunch's deviled eggs
directions: Peel and slice eggs in half.
Put yolks in bowl and whites on plate.
Mash yolks with fork; crumble bacon in yolks and other ingredients and mix well.
Use teaspoon to drop yolk mixture onto whites.
Add garnish as you like.
Makes 12.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread cubes in a 9 x 12-inch greased dish sprinkling raisins throughout.
Beat together the rest of the ingredients and pour over bread.
Allow to soak overnight, refrigerated.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake for 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: taco salad
directions: Put chips and hamburger in when ready to serve.

title: 90-minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine to 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer. Add 1/4 cup flour and beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
On floured board, knead 2 to 3 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 equal pieces. Shape into balls. Place in greased 8-inch round pan.
Pour a 1-inch depth of boiling water into a large pan on bottom rack of cold oven.
Set rolls on rack above water.
Cover. Close oven door and let rise for 30 minutes.
Uncover rolls; remove pan of water.
Turn oven to 375° and bake rolls 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Remove from pan and cool. Serve warm.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Chip margarine in casserole dish.
Spread on rice.
Spread on onion soup mix on top of rice.
Place chicken on top of soup mix. Add water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: golden frozen salad
directions: Beat mayonnaise and yogurt until smooth.
Fold in fruit cocktail, bananas and walnuts.
Pour mixture into shallow 1 1/2-quart glass freezer serving dish.
Cover and freeze until firm. Put in refrigerator 45 minutes before serving for easier cutting into squares.
You can freeze this salad inside muffin tins if you desire.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables and bacon.
Cover and seal with dressing. Sprinkle with cheese before serving.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler; stir until blended.
Stir hot milk into sugar and beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, salt and chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth and thickened, about 5 minutes.
Makes enough frosting for filling and top of 2 (9-inch) cake layers.

title: swiss steak
directions: Season steak with salt and pepper; pound flour into steak. Sear meat in hot fat; place in roaster, pour soup over meat and simmer 1 hour.
Cover meat with remaining vegetables.
Cover and cook another hour.
Remove meat and vegetables, add flour and make gravy.

title: broccoli-corn scallops
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Spread broccoli over bottom of a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, 1/2 cup crushed crackers, milk and onion.
Stir in both corns.
Spread mixture over broccoli. Combine remaining crackers and butter; sprinkle on top of vegetables.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add soups, sauce, green chilies and onions.
Crush Doritos and pour into dish.
Add mixture on top of Doritos.
Grate Cheddar cheese on top and bake until bubbly at 375°.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and almost set.
When jello is thick (not set, about 1 1/2 hours), fold remaining ingredients into it and let set.

title: banana bread muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add bananas and mix.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased or paper-lined muffin tin. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: "rolled" chicken and dumplings
directions: After chicken has been boiled, deboned and skinned, prepare your dumplings as follows.

title: the brownie sin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9-inch) round layer cake pans. Line with wax paper, extending up sides of pans.
Grease wax paper. Prepare brownies mix according to package directions for cake-like brownies, then pour mixture into prepared pans.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Cool.

title: make your own sweetened condensed milk
directions: Add dry milk to warm water.
Mix well.
Set in a pan of hot water and stir in sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
This is equal to 1 can of sweetened condensed milk.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk. Add eggs, meat, onion and seasonings.
Mix well. Form into loaf. Place in greased pan. Spread with sauce and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Line casserole dish with chips.
Layer chicken, 1/2 cup broth, soups, sliced Velveeta cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes and more cheese if you like it cheesy.
Finish with another layer of chips. Bake at 350° for about 25 or 30 minutes until bubbly and hot.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend well.

title: buttercream icing(for mom's cutouts)
directions: Mix butter, vanilla and milk; add sugar.
Spread on cookies.

title: apron strings carrot cake
directions: Combine soda, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: lentil chili
directions: Boil lentils in salt water for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes more.

title: lime pineapple punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour in 7-Up and pineapple juice.
Stir together and let sherbet melt.

title: apricot cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add apricot juice and mix well.

Chill until jelly-like consistency, then fold in the cottage cheese, walnuts, cherries, apricots and last add the whipped cream. Pour into lightly oiled 1 1/2-quart mold and chill until well set. Unmold to serve.
Makes at least 8 servings.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Bring to boil vinegar and tomato juice.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold or clear flat glass dish.
Chill until set.

title: texas cobbler(quick and easy)
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Top with other stick of margarine that has been melted.
Bake at 350° for about an hour or until golden brown on top.
Top with spoonful whipped cream or serve with a scoop of ice cream.
Servings:

title: cheesy chicken over rice
directions: In large casserole dish, combine water and uncooked rice. Stir until rice is evenly mixed in dish.
Place chicken in liquid. Cover chicken and rice with cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour pork loin
directions: Cut meat lengthwise, but not in two.
Pound until meat is 1/2 inch thick.
Cook bacon until limp.
In bacon drippings, cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Cook until thoroughly heated.
Spoon mixture into center of tenderloin.
Wrap bacon around tenderloin and secure with a toothpick.
Bake in covered roaster for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: cherry salad
directions: Chill several hours or overnight.
Keeps well in the refrigerator, if you can keep the family out of it.
It is a real favorite of everyone who has tried it.

title: bruna boner(swedish brown beans)
directions: Heat water and beans to boiling in Dutch oven. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 1 hour. Add enough water to cover beans, if necessary.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 hour. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer until beans are tender, 50 to 60 minutes.
(Add small amount of water, if necessary.)
Serves 4.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Break tuna into chunks and mix with soup, Tastee dressing and salt.
Fold mixture into cooked noodles; pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and sprinkle with a little paprika.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, syrup, cream, salt and butter in heavy saucepan.
Cook medium heat, stirring constantly, about 15 minutes, until the mixture comes to full rolling boil.
Boil hard for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat - add vanilla.
Cool - pour into jars - cover - refrigerate.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Drain green beans and cut up bacon.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a covered casserole dish 3 to 4 hours at 250° or can be put in a crock-pot on low all day.

title: angel fluff pie
directions: Blend sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice until thick. Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Pour into graham cracker or vanilla wafer crust.

title: salsa n' chips
directions: Combine everything in an airtight bowl or jar (I prefer glass). Refrigerate overnight so the flavors marry.
Serve with warm tortilla chips.

title: breadsticks
directions: Mix in blender.
Pour over breadsticks in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Stir every 1/2 hour.
Bake for 2 hours at 200°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add nuts and fruit and mix well.
Combine beaten eggs with pumpkin, oil and water.
Pour into dry ingredients and blend until just mixed.
Pour into 2 large greased and floured loaf pans to bake.
Bake at 350° until loaves pull away from sides of pans.
If batch is doubled, use a 29-ounce can of pumpkin and 1/4 cup more of flour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Wash beans well in cold water.
Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle with garlic salt and brown sugar.
Cut bacon in 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy strawberry cake
directions: Slice cake to make two layers.
Mix cream cheese frosting with vanilla cool whip.
Spread bottom layer with frosting mix. Spoon some pie filling on bottom layer.
Stack top layer on, then repeat process, covering entire cake with frosting mix.
Pour remaining pie filling into center of cake.

title: two-week slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion and pepper.
Add celery and pimentos. Sprinkle sugar on top; do not stir.
Bring other ingredients to a boil.
Pour while hot over the veggies.
Cover, without stirring; refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
The older it gets, the better. Serves 12 to 14.

title: cherry-brownie torte
directions: Grease 2 (9-inch) round layer cake pans.
Line with wax paper, extending up sides of pans; grease wax paper.
Prepare brownie mix as directed for cake-like brownies.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Cool.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil the shrimp.
Cut the bell pepper, celery and onions. Grind all together.
Use salad dressing on top.

title: rin tin tiddy
directions: In large frying pan melt butter, add chopped onion and simmer until starts to brown.
Add can tomatoes with 1 tablespoon sugar. Add salt and pepper to taste.
When hot add 6 - 8 slices cheese. When cheese is melted pour in eggs.
Stir until egg is cooked. Serve on toast.
Can add more egg if need to stretch out amount needed.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon in a large bowl; add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: holiday pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs, 1 at a time, then add flour. Stir in vanilla.
Combine fruits and nuts in 2 tablespoons flour. Stir into batter.
Pour batter in a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan, sprayed with Pam.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13 pan with whole graham crackers. Mix pudding according to package directions; add Cool Whip and cream cheese. Pour this mixture evenly over graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers; top with fudge frosting that has been slightly melted in microwave. Refrigerate and enjoy.

title: ice dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together; freeze in cups.
Serve frozen.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cream brown sugar and butter. Sift together all ingredients except vanilla, then add vanilla.

title: cow pies(yields 2 dozen)
directions: In a double boiler over simmering water, melt the chocolate chips and shortening, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in raisins and almonds.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Use 1/2 cup mix per 1/2 cup of hot water.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir into stuffing.
In an oblong casserole dish (about 12 x 6-inch), sprinkle about 1/3 of stuffing on bottom. Top with half the chicken.
Mix one of the soups with 3/4 can of chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle 1/3 stuffing.
Top with remaining chicken.
Mix other soup with 3/4 can of broth. Pour over chicken.
Top with remainder of stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix and shake good.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour half of batter into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Melt oleo, caramels and condensed milk.
Mix well and spread on cooled cake.
Put chocolate chips and pecans over top.
Then spread remaining batter over that.
Bake for 20 minutes more.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Saut the onion, celery and bell pepper in skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Cook on medium heat until tender. May have to add a little water. Brown ground beef and drain. Add onion, celery and pepper to ground beef. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix and put in casserole dish. Top with sliced cheese. Mix cream of mushroom soup or celery soup with milk. Add mixed vegetables. Pour over cheese. Cook in oven at 350° until soup is hot.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: plain pastry
directions: Place flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Add Crisco and cut in with pastry blender.
Add water carefully and stir with fork until mixture just holds together.
Roll out on slightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: hamburger - beans corn pone casserole
directions: Saute meat and onions in cooking oil until done.
Add chili powder, salt, worcestershire sauce, tomatoes, and beans.
Pour into greased 9-inch x 13-inch pan.
Follow directions for cornbread and pour over mixture.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes, or until cornbread is done.

title: cajun hot chicken
directions: Cut up chicken.
In large bowl, combine hot sauce and wine. Marinate chicken pieces 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.
Combine dry ingredients in bag.
Heat 2 cups of oil in large frying pan.
Take chicken and coat with flour mixture.
You can double coating by dredging back in liquids mix and then going back to flour.

title: governor's casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower and broccoli in boiling salted water until slightly underdone.
Drain and set aside.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter in 1-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour and blend well. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add Cheddar and Parmesan and salt and stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Place vegetables in ungreased 4-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with chopped ham.
Pour cheese sauce over all.
Make a border of buttered crumbs around edge of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cheese tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon cream cheese on each tortilla.
Top with 2 process cheese food slices and 2 or more ham slices.
Roll up tightly.
Wrap each securely in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
Cut each roll into 6 pieces; secure ends with toothpicks.
Serve with salsa or picante.
Makes 24 servings.

title: special-occasion brownie dessert
directions: Combine chocolate and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Add sugar, stirring until combined.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Stir in the eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Stir in 1 cup walnuts.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Freeze.
Thaw to slush before serving.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and oil.
Add Karo and water; stir until mixture boils rapidly.
Boil to 252° or until, when tested in cold water forms a fairly hard ball.
Add vanilla.
Pour into large platter lightly oiled with mazola; gather taffy into ball and pull.
When light in color and hard to pull; cut in 1/4ths.
Pull each piece into long strand, 1/2 inch thick.
With buttered scissors snip into bite-size pieces.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: spicy sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potato paste with sugar, cinnamon, allspice and salt.
Add eggs.
Mix milk and butter; stir into potato mixture. Mixture will be fairly liquid.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: *Use 1 cup of the sugar over fresh berries; let set 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch chocolate squares
directions: Melt shortening.
Add sugar; cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add other ingredients; blend well.
Pour into greased 11 x 15 x 3/4-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when almost cool.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Open rolls (do not separate).
Place in pan and extend over the sides.
Combine the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Place mixture on rolls and fold sides to middle; pinch closed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Before serving, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in butter until mixture is mealy.
Stir in buttermilk.
Knead lightly on slightly floured board.
Roll out; cut and bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 large biscuits.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in pan on low heat and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Mix oats, peanut butter and vanilla in mixture.
Drop on wax paper and cool.

title: great grape punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid by package directions.
