Add juice and pineapple. Makes 2 gallons.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage, breaking it up, and drain.
Mix all ingredients. Put in a 7 x 12-inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let rest for 10 minutes prior to cutting.
A little of Tony Chachere seasoning can be added.
This recipe can be altered by using more bread and/or less cheese with same results.

title: crawfish jambalaya
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in an 8 to 10-cup rice cooker. Do not add water.
Turn on cook cycle.
When the cycle is over, keep on the warm cycle for at least 30 minutes.
Do not attempt to cook this in a smaller rice cooker.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and press on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes. Let it cool. Cream together cream cheese and mayo. Mix with dill weed and garlic powder.
Spread on crust. Top with raw vegetables.

title: easy low cost eggplant parmigiana
directions: Remove the broiler pan with rack from the oven.
Have a shallow 2-1/2 quart baking dish ready.

title: raspberry cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and jell.

title: fluffy-puffy pie
directions: Microwave oleo and marshmallows in large bowl on High 1 minute (or until marshmallows melt).
Add cereal; mix quickly.
Press into bottom and sides of lightly buttered pie plate.
Cool.

title: vegetarian chopped liver *
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Cook green beans until soft.
Place eggs, onions, beans, pepper and wheat germ in bowl of food processor and process until smooth.
Refrigerate.

title: old-time potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes; cook.
Dice onion finely.
Slice eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Cut fat into flour and salt.
Add water; mix lightly.
Form into a ball; roll out on floured surface.
Line a 9-inch pie plate.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Saute Prosage, celery and onion until transparent.
Mix in rice and eggs.
Remove seeds and stem from peppers and parboil them for 5 minutes.
Set peppers in a greased casserole and fill with rice mixture.
Don't crowd peppers as they will swell some in baking. If there is some rice mix left over, it can be placed in between peppers.
Top with French fried onion rings that come in a can.

title: baked lake trout
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour to make a paste.
Place 3 slices of bacon in bottom of pan; cover with onion and crumbled bay leaf. Place fish on top.
Spread flour paste and butter on fish; sprinkle on bread crumbs and place remaining bacon, sliced, on top.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: peaches n' cream cheesecake
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 9 pie pan.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, butter, egg, and milk.
Beat for 2 minutes. Pour into pan.
Place peaches on top of batter.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and reserved peach juice, beat 2 minutes.
Spoon to within 1 inch of edge of batter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon, sprinkle over cheese.
Bake 350° for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving.
Serves 6.

title: granny's hucklebbery buckle
directions: Add to sugar/shortening mixture.
Add 2 c. berries and pour into square greased pan.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, syrup and salt and boil 5 minutes. Add soda and vanilla and pour over popcorn, stirring thoroughly. Put on lightly greased cookie sheets and bake for 1 hour at 200°. Turn every 15 minutes.

title: curried rice
directions: Place in saucepan; bring to boil.
Lower heat.
Cook until water is absorbed, about 10 minutes.
Fluff with fork; add 2 tablespoons oleo.
Pour gently on platter.
Place chicken strips in mound on top.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, mix nuts and coconut in bottom of pan. Prepare cake mix according to box directions. Pour batter on top of nuts/coconut. Melt margarine and mix with cream cheese. Add powdered sugar and pour over batter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, nutmeg, cloves, ginger and cinnamon.
Cream margarine with sugar and molasses until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk and then add flour mixture.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick. Cut with cookie cutters and bake at 350° approximately 12 to 15 minutes.
Top with gingerbread frosting after cooled.

title: beef garden casserole
directions: Cook onion in small amount of oil until tender, not brown.
Add ground beef and seasoning.
Brown lightly.
Drain.
Add okra, green beans, corn and tomato soup.
Bake into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: hershey's cocoa fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add milk slowly.
Put on medium heat; stir occasionally.
When it forms a soft ball in cold water, remove from heat.
Add 1/2 stick butter and the vanilla.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered dish.
Let set 10 minutes.

title: berried delight
directions: Prepare crust by mixing together ingredients, press firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: golden crumb broccoli(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Place drained broccoli into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese, pimento and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli. Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix Russian dressing, preserves and onion soup together; marinate chicken overnight, turning occasionally.
Bake
1 1/2 hours at 350°, covered; turn once.
Serve with rice.

title: pumpkin patch pie
directions: Place sherbet in bowl; stir until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 of Cool Whip until well blended.
(For more intense orange color, stir in a few drops of red and yellow food coloring.)
Spoon into crust. Sprinkle with chopped Oreo cookies, pressing firmly into sherbet. Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm. Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with finely chopped Oreo cookies and candy pumpkins if desired. Store leftover pie in freezer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs at high speed until thick and light. Combine sugar and oil.
Beat into eggs.
Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture along with vanilla.
Stir in walnuts.

title: busy day stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown ground meat; set aside.
Place chopped cabbage into a greased 4-quart casserole dish.
Pour ground meat over cabbage. Pour the undiluted soup over the meat.
Cover.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: bayou bounty seafood casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese and 1/2 cup margarine together.

Saute onions, green pepper, celery and mushrooms in remaining margarine. Add shrimp. Saute until shrimp are pink. Add crabmeat, soup, rice and seasonings. Mix well. Stir in cream cheese mixture. Spoon into shallow 3-quart casserole dish. Top with shredded cheese and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: tomato soup
directions: In Dutch oven, saute celery, onion, carrot and green pepper in margarine.
Stir in 4 cups broth, tomatoes, curry powder, salt, pepper and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tomatoes are tender. Combine flour and 1/4 cup broth. Stir into soup until thickened.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: instant spice tea mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store in a dry place.
To use, put 2 or 3 teaspoons of mixture per 8 ounces of hot water.

title: prune cake with praline topping
directions: Stir together flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and salt; set aside.
In large bowl beat at high speed thoroughly with sugar, oil and eggs.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix just until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in prunes and pecans.
Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake in center of 325° oven about 1 hour or until pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool pan on rack.
Spread with topping.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: strawberry figs
directions: Mix sugar, figs and jello.
Stir well.
Cook over low heat until mixture bubbles.
Cook from 45 to 55 minutes.
Stir often. Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: low-fat spice layer cake
directions: Combine yellow cake mix, egg whites, water and fat-free mayonnaise in a large bowl.
Beat on low speed with electric mixer until blended.
Add cinnamon, allspice, ginger and nutmeg.
Beat on high speed 2 minutes.

title: quickie muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease muffin tins well (pour Wesson oil in one well of tin, use paper towel, dip and grease other wells).
Mix yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add egg and other ingredients.
Mix by hand with wooden spoon.
This is a very soft, gooey dough.
Fill muffin tins about 3/4 full and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown on top.
Excess dough can be stored covered in refrigerator for up to 4 weeks.

title: tuna log
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: green chili
directions: Brown Pork, then add all other ingredients.
Cook on low for 4 hours.
Serve over any of your favorite mexican food or with a flour tortilla.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; let cool.
Mix all other ingredients with macaroni.
Stir well.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight and serve.

title: cry babies
directions: Cream sugar with shortening.
Add eggs, beaten, then add molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with liquids.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add pineapple juice and milk and mix well.
Add pineapple chunks and bread cubes.
Fold in carefully.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be made ahead and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: golden bars
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Melt butter, remove from heat and stir in rest of ingredients.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Place cooked macaroni in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add milk and cubed cheese.
Let stand in a warm place for 30 minutes.
Add eggs; stir well and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: low-fat pound cake
directions: Combine margarine and sugar; beat until smooth.
Add egg whites and vanilla; beat.
In separate bowl, combine flour, oat bran and baking soda.
Add flour mixture and yogurt to margarine mixture.
Beat just enough to mix well.
Coat an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Let sit for 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: steak(pan fried)
directions: Sprinkle steaks lightly with salts and peppers.
Place in skillet one pat of butter for each steak.
On medium heat, fry on each side until lightly brown.
Place chopped onion and parsley on top of steaks.
Pour in about 1 tablespoon of wine for each steak. Cover and simmer until cooked to your taste.

title: olga's dumplings
directions: Beat together egg and water.
Add flour until you have a stiff dough.
Roll in wax paper and put in freezer.
Chill through and through.
Roll out paper thin and cut into dumplings.
Dry out overnight or 1 1/2 hours in refrigerator.
Drop a few dumplings at a time into the broth.
Have broth at a rolling boil.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown chops (no grease).
Take out of pan.
Add 1/2 cup water to drippings.
Add cream of celery soup.
Place chops in baking dish.
Cover with sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry-banana pie
directions: Layer a 9 x 13-inch plate with graham crackers.
Slice strawberries and bananas on top.
Mix Cool Whip and yogurts; layer on top of pie.
Let chill.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Moisten dry ingredients with part milk.
Add to remaining milk and cook about 8 minutes.
Blend in beaten egg yolks and butter. When well blended and thickened, add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool and place in baked crust.
Add meringue made of egg whites, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Place on top of pie with fork to form peaks.
Bake meringue in slow oven until browned.

title: sausage rice bake
directions: Place all ingredients in a greased oblong pan. Mix well.
Make sure it is covered. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: feta shrimp
directions: Fry onions and/or garlic until transparent.
Add shrimp and cook until they turn pink.
Add olives, wine, lemon juice and Feta cheese.
Put in casserole and bake in 350° oven until hot.
Do not cook too long.
Do not want to melt Feta cheese.

title: devilishly decadent pudding cake(very low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat 8-inch square baking pan with vegetable cooking spray; set aside.
Mix thoroughly the milk, applesauce, flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons of cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Spread evenly in pan.

title: microwave japanese stew
directions: You should be able to find the soy sauce, rice wine, and dashi in the Asian section of the grocery store.

title: sausage wraps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Cut each triangle lengthwise into thirds.
Place sausages on shortest side of each triangle.
Roll up from shortest side to opposite point.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 48.

title: mexican egg roll
directions: Fry meat and onion in skillet, adding garlic salt to taste. Drain well.

title: carla's quiche
directions: *You can use different kinds or all one kind, as long as it is a hard cheese.

title: white bean and vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, heat olive oil over moderately high heat and cook onion, celery, bay leaf, thyme and rosemary, stirring occasionally until onion and celery are translucent.
Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute.
Add carrots, red potatoes, beans, stock and 5 cups water; bring soup to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer soup covered for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Stir in the wine and additional stock or water to achieve desired consistency.
Remove bay leaf.
In a blender, puree 2 cups of the soup until smooth and stir into soup.
Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper and stir in parsley.
Serve soup with Parmesan.
Yields 10 to 12 cups.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make holes and pour in mixed oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour over all water.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and stir in mandarin oranges.
Bake.
Cool cake for 30 to 35 minutes.
While cake is baking, place 1 can of pineapple in saucepan.
Add cornstarch and stir until thick.
Let cool.
Mix pudding with milk and add Cool Whip.
On cool cake, layer as follows:
spread pineapple, sliced bananas and Cool Whip pudding.
Top with pecans and cherries.

title: mint butter
directions: Serve with potatoes, carrots and peas.

title: ground meat and rice
directions: Brown ground meat until all pink color is gone.
Add the onions, celery and bell pepper.
Stir to mix and saute vegetables a little.
Add the water and bouillon cubes.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add the rice and mushrooms, simmer until rice is done.

title: gracious hot salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on medium heat for 2 1/2 hours, stirring often, to keep from sticking.
(Cook longer if you want it thicker.)
Put in canning jars while hot.
Use sealing lids.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix vinegar with milk and set aside.
Mix shortening into flour and salt mixture until crumbly.
Add milk-vinegar mixture. The dough will be very soggy.
Use flour to roll a rich, flaky never fail pie crust.

title: oven fried pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Trim fat from chops. Combine breadcrumbs, Italian seasoning, paprika, and dash of garlic powder in a shallow dish; stir well. Dip chops in juice mixture. Place chops on a broiler pan coated with cooking spray. Bake a 350 degrees for 50 minutes. Makes 4 servings, 5 points each.

title: california vegetables
directions: Place frozen California mix vegetables in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Leave for 2 minutes; drain and cool.
Chop olives, mushrooms, tomatoes, celery and onions.
Combine dressing, vinegar and oil; pour this over vegetables.
Cover and set in refrigerator at least 24 hours.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Blend first 4 items together and spread in a thin layer on the tortilla shell, then
layer
with
ham	and
roll
up. Refrigerate overnight for easy slicing.

title: oyster stew
directions: In a 4-quart boiler, heat butter, Worcestershire sauce and celery.
Add oysters.
Cook until edges curl.
Add oysters, juice, milk and spices to taste.
Heat until hot.
Do not boil.

title: angel food cake
directions: Separate egg whites, let whites stand at room temperature about 1 hour.
Set oven at 375° to preheat.
Sift together 4 times, flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
In a large bowl, combine egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and flavorings.
Beat on speed No. 12 until whites are stiff and stand at peaks 2 minutes.
Do not overbeat until dry. Sprinkle in rapidly while beating on speed No. 8. Add the remaining 1 cup of sugar about 1 minute, scraping bowl gently toward beaters with rubber spatula.
Turn to speed No. 1; sprinkle in sifted flour mixture evenly and quickly, scraping up and over with folding motion only until blended, about 1 1/2 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Pour into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake 1 hour or until bubbly in 350° oven.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix each of the above listed ingredients together, except for the crackers and butter.
Crush the crackers; add the butter to it.
Sprinkle the cracker crumbs on top of the casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Layer all in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
First layer is crushed graham crackers.
Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Next add chocolate chips, then butterscotch chips.
Add peanuts next and then coconut.
Lastly, pour condensed milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Allow to cool and cut in squares.

title: danish blue lamb chops
directions: Preheat broiler.
If using rib chops, trim and scrape rib bones.
Brush chops with oil; sprinkle with pepper and garlic. Leave for a couple of hours, if possible, before broiling.
Mix cheese and cream; mash well together to form paste.
Broil chops 5 to 6 minutes on each side; remove from heat.
Spread cheese mixture on one side of each chop.
Replace under heat until cheese is light brown and bubbling.
Makes 4 servings.

title: co-op student home cookin'
directions: Combine all ingredients except instant grits in large saucepan.
Heat.
Add enough instant grits to solidify the mixture.
Serve warm.

title: le~roy's hot weenies
directions: Put in crock-pot. Cook on medium heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until ends puff up.

title: toffee
directions: Boil butter and sugar in a pan until it changes color 3 times, about 9 minutes.
Pour out onto ungreased cookie sheet; spread out.
Break up Hershey bars on top; spread with spatula.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Roll into large balls and dip into sugar.
Bake at 350 degrees until brown (12 - 15 minutes).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and pour over stuffing mix.
Let stand 15 minutes.

In the meantime, mix together the rest of ingredients. In a shallow buttered casserole, layer stuffing and chicken salad. Cover with 1 can mushroom soup (undiluted), then sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop stir-fry
directions: Cut pork chops into strips.
Heat a little oil in skillet; brown the pork.
Add peppers, mushrooms and onions and cook until done, stirring as it goes.
Add a little soy sauce and it's ready.

title: 9 layer dip
directions: Brown ground beef with taco seasoning; drain fat.
Layer in 9 x 12-inch glass dish:
refried beans, guacamole, beef, 1/2 sour cream and cheese.
Heat in 350° oven 15 minutes until warm and cheese is melted.
Top with 1/2 sour cream, lettuce, tomatoes and olives. Serve with large bag nacho chips.

title: grahams and pudding
directions: Make pudding according to directions on box, but do not cool. Arrange 1 layer of graham crackers on bottom of a 6 x 8-inch glass or metal (nonaluminum) baking dish.
Pour 1/2-inch layer of chocolate pudding on top of graham crackers, then another layer of graham crackers and pudding.
Repeat, but make sure the last layer is pudding.
Refrigerate until set and serve.

title: diet applesauce cookies
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well with spoon.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Boil together for 15 minutes sugar, water, raisins and Crisco.
When cool, add flour sifted with cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Add baking soda to mixture.
Bake slowly in low oven (275°) 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until done.
To make a richer cake add candied citron, orange, lemon, pineapple and candied cherries.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Add hamburg; cook until brown. Add all other ingredients except noodles and cheese.
Heat to a boil; simmer 15 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place uncooked noodles.
Cover with hamburg mixture; swirl together.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Cut in squares.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix flour, butter and 1 cup of pecans.
(If needed, you can add more flour.)
Put in pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool crust.

title: oyster stew
directions: Simmer oysters in own fluid, plus 1/4 cup water.
Skim! Add cup milk plus whole milk plus butter.
Add Greek seasoning. Continue to simmer 6 minutes adding several sprinkles of celery, garlic and onion salt.
Garnish with parsley flakes.
Serve with oyster crackers (2 large bowls), stirring throughout.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Melt chocolate and stir into egg mixture.
Add zucchini.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Layer sausage and bread.
Pour eggs and milk mixture over sausage and bread.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups shredded cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight or bake at once for 25 minutes at 325°.
Makes enough for 6 or 8 people.
Can be frozen for several weeks.
Rewarm and serve.

title: buddy's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a small heavy saucepan and bring to a rapid boil.
Foam will form on top.
Lower heat to medium boil and stir until foam disappears.
Bastes 3 chickens.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cucumber cheese dip
directions: Coarsely grate peeled cucumber; drain, reserving liquid.
Stir and soften cream cheese; add lemon juice.
Stir in onion and cucumber.

title: mom's great rice dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients raw, except green onions and parsley, in a large pot.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. Stir and bake another 30 minutes.
Add parsley and green onions and bake another 15 minutes.

title: paper bag barbecue chicken
directions: Open a heavy paper bag (no holes in it).
Place in large baking pan on its side.
Brush melted shortening over inside of bag with pastry brush; cover well.
Place chicken pieces, skin up, in single layer on the bottom of the bag.
Spoon barbecue sauce evenly over chicken.
Fold open end of bag over twice.
Secure closure with paper clips.
Place pan in cold oven.
Set oven at 350°.
Bake for 1 3/4 hours; do not open bag during cooking.
Remove pan.
Slit open bag.
Remove chicken to platter.
Spoon extra sauce from bag over chicken.
Serve.

title: pepperoni beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven over low heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour stirring occasionally.
I put mine in the crock-pot for the day!

title: stuff and clutter
directions: Use two large roaster pans to heat in oven.
Mix first seven ingredients.
Melt butter and bacon grease with remaining ingredients.
Pour over cereal mixture, stirring to coat all ingredients.
Bake at 300° until brown (1 hour).
Cool completely before putting in airtight containers.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: peach fried pies
directions: Cook peaches,
sugar and 2 cups of water.
It will take 3 hours
to
cook
until
tender
and
put about 2 tablespoons cinnamon in peaches. Do not use hot, let cool in refrigerator.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken pieces in egg and milk mixture.
Coat with bread crumbs and/or seasonings.
Brown chicken pieces.
Cover with spaghetti sauce. Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Put back in the oven just until cheese melts.
Serve over pasta.

title: fresh spinach-apple salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach; wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry. Tear into bite size pieces.
Combine spinach, apple and celery in large bowl.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; toss well.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over spinach mixture; toss well.
Serve immediately. Serves 12.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating thoroughly with each addition.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch square cake pan for 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar and eggs and mix well. Add milk and blend well and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: zucchini pie(better than apple!)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel zucchini.
Cut lengthwise and remove seeds.
Cut in pieces to look like apples for apple pie. (Optional:
Cook or steam briefly if softer fruit is desired.
Cool well in cold water and drain well before adding.)
Stir together dry ingredients.
Mix lightly with zucchini.
Turn into pastry lined pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Flute edge and cut slits in top.
Brush top with milk and sprinkle cinnamon-sugar.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: apricot rolls
directions: Soften cream cheese and oleo in microwave.
Mix ingredients. Roll on floured surface.
Cut in squares.
Fill with apricot filling.
Pinch shut.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° to 375° until light brown.

title: mincemeat pastries
directions: Combine sugar, oats, flour and salt; mix well. Cut in shortening to the consistency of coarse crumbs.
Spread half of this mixture in shallow pan (7 x 11 x 2-inch). Cover with mincemeat.
Spread with remaining half of mixture on top.

title: maple pralines
directions: Boil maple syrup, milk and sugar until soft ball forms in cold water.
Add butter and chopped nuts. Beat until thick and smooth. Drop by spoonful onto greased sheet or wax paper.

title: olie bolen
directions: Mix well.
Prepare oil to 375°.
Drop by tablespoons into deep, hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple into well-greased (13 x 9 x 2-inch) dish or pan.
Pour cherry pie filling over pineapple and spread well.
Dump cake mix over pie filling and spread well.
Slice margarine thin and layer over top of cake mix.
Put into 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Take from oven and sprinkle nuts over top of cake.
Put in oven until brown.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake corn muffin mix according to package directions and cool. Crumble in a large bowl.
Add tomato, cucumber, onion and green pepper to the cornbread and mix.
Stir in enough mayonnaise to moisten the mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken wings
directions: Marinate all ingredients 24 hours in refrigerator, then drain and bake 1 hour
on a cookie sheet at 350°.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar, Wesson oil, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and eggs (added one at a time).
Pour half batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Make mixture of 3 teaspoons brown sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 cup chopped nuts and sprinkle over batter in pan.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: salad #1
directions: Put it in a bowl, then eat it!

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop or shred cabbage and cook until tender in salted water. Drain well.
Melt butter in large pan; add soup, milk, mayonnaise, cheese and pepper.
Mix together.
Add cooked cabbage and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle crushed cracker crumbs over and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: jalapeno-glazed turkey breast
directions: Grill turkey according to manufacturer's directions, about 45 minutes to 2 hours or until meat thermometer reaches 170°.
(Could also prepare in oven.)

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 prepared loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until brown.

title: christmas peppermint cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix in extract, flavoring and salt.
Add flour and buttermilk in small amounts, stirring well.
When batter is thoroughly mixed, add crushed candy and stir throughout gently.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: trio fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Blend in remaining ingredients with whisk.
Cook until thickened.
Chill.
Dressing may be served plain or folded into whipped cream for fruit salad. Pineapple, apples, bananas and marshmallows make a good combination.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and mix in a 2-quart greased casserole with tomatoes and mushrooms.
Heat and stir the rest of the ingredients until the cheese melts.
Pour over the macaroni and bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: kitchen floor pickles
directions: Add the salt, alum, spices and vinegar to the gallon of pickles.
Finish filling with water.
Put cap on jar and let set for 1 month.
After 1 month, remove cucumbers from jar and wash thoroughly (jar also).
Cut cucumbers into chunks and put back into jar.
Add sugar and shake jar to coat cucumbers and continue to shake until sugar melts and covers cucumbers with juice.
Pickles are ready to eat.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in Cajun seasoning.
Add chicken and saute for 8 to 10 minutes per side or until thoroughly cooked.

title: carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Mix all dry ingredients together. Add carrots, nuts, oil, eggs and mix well. Grease two
(or three small) loaf pans. Place mixture in pans. bake 35-60 minutes or when tooth pick comes out clean.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter, and vanilla flavoring.
Add flour until a stiff dough is obtained.
Roll into logs.
Chill.
Slice off and bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: sweet `n' sour chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a medium sized bowl, mix together the dressing, preserves and onion soup. Place the chicken in a 9 x 13 baking pan. Pour the dressing mixture over the chicken. Bake for 25 minutes, covered, then uncover and bake for 20 minutes more or until the chicken is fork-tender and no pink remains.

title: biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
(It's better if the shortening is worked into flour with one's fingers.)
Add milk, working into a soft dough. Biscuits may be rolled or "pinched off" as I do.

title: spicy hot wings
directions: Defrost chicken wings, soak overnight in hot peppers and juice.
Bake at 350° in aluminum pan for 40 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Heat and melt margarine and entire bottle of hot sauce. Pour over wings and put in broiler for 10 minutes until crispy brown.
Serve with Blue cheese or Ranch dressing.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Mix together candy bars and pecans; set aside.
Mix together the egg yolks, butter, powdered sugar and large Cool Whip; set aside.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; spread 1/2 cake pieces on bottom of pan.
Top with 1/2 Cool Whip mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 candy mixture.
Repeat end with candy mixture on top.
Chill overnight.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Saute and drain hamburger, onion, celery and bell pepper.
Add Ranch Style beans, water, tomatoes, chili powder and cabbage. Salt to taste.
Cook until cabbage is done.

title: rhubarb strawberry pie
directions: In 3 quart saucepan, heat rhubarb, cinnamon and 2 tablespoons water to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until rhubarb is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in strawberry gelatin, stirring until gelatin completely dissolves. Remove saucepan from heat; stir in sugar to taste.
Cover and refrigerate until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon, abut 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour rhubarb mixture into baked shell.
Refrigerate until filling is set (about 3 hours).
To serve:
slice each strawberry in half and arrange on pie.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.
Thoroughly combine completely thawed strawberries and syrup with dry gelatin; set aside.
(No need to sift flour.
Measure by lightly spooning into cup and leveling off.)
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Pour batter evenly over marshmallows in prepared pan.
Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cool with ice cream or whipped cream.
(Omit baking powder and salt if using Pillsbury's Best self-rising flour.)

title: fudge sauce
directions: Heat the butter and chocolate in double boiler over simmering water until melted.
Stir in salt, then sugar in 4 or 5 portions being sure to blend in sugar thoroughly after each portion.
The mixture becomes very thick, dry and grainy.
Now stir in milk very slowly, then cook 5 or 6 minutes longer until slightly thickened, stirring often.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Pour into glass jars with tight fitting lids. Cover and cool, then store in refrigerator.

title: barbecue sauce(made famous in the 1920's)
directions: Heat oil; add all ingredients except pepper and paprika.
Mix until smooth.
Add soup stock or water to thin.
Cook over low heat until thick consistency of gravy.
Can be reduced into smaller portion.
Cut ingredients by 1/2 or 1/4.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Divide into 24 balls.
Press in tiny muffin tins.
Put 3 pecan halves in each.
Pour the following mixture over this.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Simmer chicken breasts, 1 stick margarine, chicken bouillon and spices in stock pot with sufficient water to cover for about 4 hours.
Remove chicken and bay leaves.
Cool chicken and dice. Saute onion in 2 tablespoons margarine until transparent.
Combine the flour and 4 tablespoons margarine in skillet; cook until slightly browned.
Take pot with chicken broth off fire.
Add roux; stir until thickened.
Add onion, diced chicken and Veg-All. Pour into baking dish.
Cover with crescent roll dough.
Bake according to instructions on roll can.

title: tex-mex lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, make the sauce by browning the beef with the onion, drain the liquid; add the tomato paste, picante sauce, water, oregano and basil.
Mix well and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine the Ricotta cheese and 3/4 cup of Mozzarella cheese; set aside.
Coat a 7 x 11-inch baking pan with non-stick vegetable spray.
Layer the ingredients in the pan as follows:
1/3 cup of sauce, half of the uncooked noodles and half of the Ricotta cheese mixture; repeat the layers and top with remaining sauce then the remaining 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, uncover and bake in a pre-heated 350° oven for 1 hour, or until light golden, remove from the oven and let stand for 20 minutes for easier serving.

title: diet cake
directions: Cook raisins until water is gone.
Mix applesauce, eggs, liquid sweetener and oil together.
Mix well.
Mix dry ingredients to applesauce mixture.
Blend well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour in cake pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat in a medium bowl with wooden spoon the sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg until creamy and well blended.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cut into 2-inch bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: pecan cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until real stiff.
Add sugar and beat real good.
Add 1 teaspoon baking powder and vanilla.
Roll crackers on cloth until really fine. Pour all in bowl and mix real good. Add pecans. Pour in pie pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Crush crackers with rolling pin.
Mix crumbs with milk and let soften.
Add egg, salt, pepper, onion, nutmeg and meat mixture. Blend gently, but well.
Roll into balls an inch in diameter. Heat oil in skillet and saute meatballs until brown, about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan, discard oil and wipe pan.
Then prepare sauce.

title: merry berry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With mixer, beat flour, oats, 3/4 cup sugar and butter until crumbly.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups of the mixture; press remaining mixture on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: applesauce muffins(dietary)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in bowl by hand until smooth.
Bake in 6 muffin tins which have been sprayed with Pam, 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry orange mold
directions: Dissolve jello; set aside.
Grind apple and orange.
Stir all ingredients together until well mixed.
Put in mold or bowl; refrigerate to set.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: shandy gaff(non-alcoholic)
directions: Into hot tea add sugar and lemon juice.
Chill.
Add ginger ale and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: "easy as pie" apple pie
directions: Coat apples with sugar and cinnamon.
Melt oleo.
Add to apples.
Pour flour and sugar over apples; stir.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Separate eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Scald milk. Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix ground beef, onion, bell pepper, bread crumbs and tomato paste together.
After it is all mixed up, put it in a pan, pat it all together and then put ketchup on top of it.
Cook 1 hour.

title: ranch dip flavored pretzels
directions: Break pretzels into bite-sized pieces.
Combine oil and dressing mix.
Pour over pretzels.
Let stand, stirring occasionally, until all oil is absorbed by the pretzels.

title: jo's sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake on greased sheet 45 minutes at 300°.
Cover with foil.
May be frozen after baking.
If so, leave foil on and heat at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 60 balls.

title: baby spring salad mix
directions: Cut up tomatoes and green onions.
Then mix all of the salad ingredients together.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until tender.
Drain and combine with tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
Blend together soup, milk, cheese;
heat and stir until cheese is melted.
Add to noodle mix.
Pour into a 2 quart casserole and top with almonds. Bake uncovered at 425 degrees for 20 minutes, or until bubbling starts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy salmon casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add salt, pepper and
mustard.
Mix well.
Add bread crumbs and stir until butter mixture is absorbed.
Add milk, eggs and liquid from salmon.
Add salmon and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm and brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix shredded cabbage and grated carrots in a large bowl.
Mix up Miracle Whip, milk and sugar.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Carefully take a spoon and hollow out the mushroom, keep the scrapings. In a skillet brown sausage, onion and mushroom scrapings. Drain. Add Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, garlic and parsley to the pan - mix well with sausage, remove from heat and stuff mushrooms. Put mushrooms in a baking dish, sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Bake 15 minutes.

title: tuna ball
directions: Cream together and chill.
Roll in parsley and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Microwave the sugar and Karo syrup on High for 4 minutes.
Add nuts; stir.
Cook on High another 4 minutes.
Add the butter and vanilla and cook on High again for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir quickly until foamy and pour into well-greased pan.
Do not use butter to grease pan.
Allow to cool and break apart.

title: gingerbread men
directions: In a sauce pan, bring sugar, molasses and butter to a boil. Let cool 5 minutes.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Lightly grease or spray with Pam a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Spread undrained pineapple over bottom of dish.
Add a layer of blueberries and 3/4 cup of sugar.
Sprinkle box of cake mix on top of fruit.
Drizzle melted butter over dry cake mix.
Top with nuts and 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake
mix is done.
About 25 minutes into cooking time, cut down through mixture in several places.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix vegetables and bacon. Cover. Put in refrigerator while mixing dressing. Combine dressing ingredients. Pour over vegetables 1 hour before serving.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: roasted chicken with herbs
directions: Heat margarine and oil in rectangular pan in a 375° oven until margarine is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except chicken.
Place chicken, skin side up, in pan.
Coat with mixture. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: meat loaf with glaze
directions: Mix together and pour over meat loaf. Continue baking for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cream cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Blend 1 cup fruit and yogurt with enough milk, water or juice to make a milkshake consistency.
Drink and enjoy!

title: bourbon apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix apples and bourbon.
Add sugar mixture, pecans and raisins to apples.
Mix.
Line a greased 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Paint bottom with apricot glaze (jar apricot preserves and 4 tablespoons apricot brandy or orange liqueur).
Heap apple mixture in pastry.
Dot with butter.
Roll remaining pastry; place on top of apples, flute edges and cut vents in top pastry to allow steam to escape.
Brush top crust with milk and dust with sugar. Bake in lower third of oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until crust is browned and apples tender.

title: hearty cabbage soup
directions: Saute beef, onions, garlic, celery and pepper in oil; add remaining ingredients except cabbage.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Add cabbage.
Simmer for 1 more hour, adding more water, up to 3 cups, if necessary.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken, onions and bouillon in stockpot. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cut and clean vegetables. Remove chicken from pot and cut up and remove bones from chicken. Cook vegetables in chicken broth. Add clean, cut up chicken and noodles.

title: cran-apple muffins
directions: Combine cranberry sauce and orange peel. Set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Make a well in center.
Combine egg, apple, milk and oil.
Add egg mixture all at once to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened. Fill greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups 1/2 full.
Make a well in center of each with back of spoon. Spoon 2 teaspoons of cranberry filling into each well. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Combine 10x sugar and juice to make drizzling consistency.
Drizzle over warm muffins.
Makes 12.

title: parmesan chicken(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray baking dish with nonstick spray. Remove fat from chicken; dip in warm water.
Roll in combined bread crumbs, cheese, salt, pepper and paprika.
Place into prepared dish.
Spray with spray lightly.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugars; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Blend in flour, salt and soda.
Chill dough for 20 minutes.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass that has been greased and dipped in sugar.
Dip glass in sugar to flatten each cookie.
Make cookies thin.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Keeps in refrigerator for a few weeks.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cranberries and sugar; let stand 30 minutes.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Gently fold in the whipped cream.
Chill before serving.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: In blender or food processor, add Special K, Parmesan cheese, flour and Italian seasoning. Blend until cereal resembles fine crumbs. Place in shallow dish; set aside. Pour salad dressing into another shallow dish. Dip chicken in salad dressing; coat with cereal mixture. Place in single layer in baking pan coated with vegetable oil. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Do not cover or turn chicken while baking.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together until creamy and use on your choice of raw vegetables.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, butter, sugar, vanilla and pudding mix in large bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs and flour mixture.
Add chips and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 2-inches apart, onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.
For chocolate cookies, use chocolate instant pudding mix.

title: aunt ceil's chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour, pour in milk, then margarine; mix together.
Add eggs and mix.
Then add flavorings and mix.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake 25 minutes until done or set.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mash 3 peaches; add sugar, cornstarch and orange juice. Cook until
thick;
add butter and cool.
Slice 4 peaches into baked crust.
Pour mix over sliced peaches.
Refrigerate.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in margarine, stirring constantly on medium heat until melted.
Mix popcorn, gumdrops and peanuts.
Pour melted marshmallows over corn mixture; mix thoroughly.
Pack in buttered tube pan.
Keep in cool place, but do not refrigerate.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together the cream cheese and 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Add the chicken, milk, pepper and onion; mix well.
Separate each package of crescent rolls into four rectangles.
Divide the chicken filling evenly and spoon into center of each rectangle.
Bring ends up together and pinch closed.
Brush with remaining 2 tablespoons of melted butter.
Place puffs on a greased cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Let stand.
Add oil.
Beat eggs and vanilla.
Add apples and dry ingredients.
Put in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions in a gallon jug.
Put spices and sugar over mixture.
Heat
vinegar	and
salt.
Pour
over mixture.
Sugar may be added
a little at a time as vinegar is poured over mixture.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: carolyn schnarr's hot curried fruit
directions: Drain all fruits well and place in a casserole dish.
In a saucepan, combine margarine, brown sugar, curry and cinnamon. Simmer 1-2 minutes and pour over fruit.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add applesauce and mix well. Add rest of ingredients, mixed.
Bake in well-greased paper-lined pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and garlic in oil in skillet. Drain the meat and add the tomato sauce, tomato paste, 1/2 can water, salt, pepper and oregano. Cover skillet and simmer 1 hour.
Cook the lasagna noodles (with the 1 tablespoon salad oil to keep noodles from sticking). Drain.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until meat is lightly browned. Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir so tomatoes become slightly mashed.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Adjust seasoning.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Cook chopped onion in microwave for two minutes.
Put all ingredients, except bread, in a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly and then mix in bread last.
Grease a crock-pot.
Pour dressing into crock-pot, alternating chicken or turkey, if desired.
Put a small amount of butter or margarine on top of dressing (1/4 cup).
Cook 4 hours on low or 2 hours on high.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: chunk pickles
directions: Peel and remove seeds the night before.
Cut into desired size.
Sprinkle generously with salt and let stand overnight. Drain.
Let syrup come to a boil, then add cukes.
Cook until cukes change color (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Pack in jars and seal.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into pieces. Combine flour and salt.
Fry meat in hot shortening. Drain off excess fat.
Add undrained tomatoes, onion, celery, carrot and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and cook over low heat about 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender. Remove meat to a serving platter.
Keep warm.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Pour butter, oil and spice mixture over shrimp. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes. Broil 5 minutes until shrimp are white.

title: blueberry cake(beverly slimm)
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, milk, baking soda, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Add blueberries.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, depending on your oven.

title: prune kuka
directions: Mix together brown sugar, 3 tablespoons flour and cinnamon. Sprinkle on top of prunes.
Place in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch high greased and floured pan.
Mix the balance of the ingredients and pour on top of the prune mixture except for the melted butter which is to be poured on top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
(Use German tree ripened prunes.)

title: chewy blond brownies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: mississippi caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients together 1 to 2 days ahead.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 400° until brown and bubbly (approximately 40 to 45 minutes).

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except oatmeal, in saucepan on stove.
Boil together until blended well.
Lower heat to simmer, then add gradually oatmeal until thick.
Drop by spoonful and refrigerate.

title: lee's fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a slow boil.
Boil one minute. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and marshmallow.
Let stand overnight.
Cut and serve.

title: my meat loaf
directions: Mix together well; add cracker crumbs until mixture holds together.
Place on rack in covered pan.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: french apple pie
directions: Grease deep dish pie plate or large Corning Ware dish.
Put in pie filling and sprinkle with cinnamon to taste.
In medium size bowl, mix milk, Bisquick, eggs and margarine.
Beat on high for 1 minute.
Pour mixture over pie filling.
Sprinkle with Streusel.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, milk, cocoa and vanilla in saucepan and bring to boil.
Boil for 4 minutes.
Do not hard boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter; add oats slowly (may not need to use all 3 cups).
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let cool 1 hour.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar and spices and add butter.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for about 50 minutes.

title: pickled dill beans
directions: Combine first nine (9) ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 3 minutes.
Wash and trim beans.
Do not blanch.
Pack beans in sterile jars.
Pour vinegar solution over beans.
Seal.
Process in water bath for 10 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and beat until light.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Drain clams, reserving juice.
Set clams aside.
Combine clam juice and remaining ingredients in a saucepan; cook over low heat until cream cheese melts stirring occasionally.
Stir in clams. Serve hot with crackers.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, yogurt and milk.
Beat thoroughly with a wooden spoon. Add the honey and oil.
Add the dry ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease baking dish with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes with aluminum foil covering.
Layer casserole as follows: Place stuffing on bottom of baking dish, lay chicken out on top of stuffing, put Mozzarella cheese all over and more stuffing on top. Bake.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir in yeast.
Knead 5 minutes until smooth.
Let rise until double.
Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut doughnuts with cutter.
Let rise 30 to 35 minutes. Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels. Dust with sugar, if desired.
Yields about 24 doughnuts.

title: ez chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie crusts according to directions on box.
Mix pie filling according to directions on box.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken spinach quiche(yields 6 servings)
directions: Spread pie crust with butter.
In saucepan, over medium heat, melt 2 tablespoons butter, adding scallion, and cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; set aside.

title: aunt connie's potato casserole
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients.
Mix cornflakes and butter and use to top casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil noodles. Drain off water. Run cool water over noodles. Drain again. Cube cucumber, tomato and onion. Mix with noodles and pour dressing over noodles. Mix well. Nice cookout salad.

title: whole wheat soft pretzels
directions: Stir together yeast, warm water and sugar in a bowl.
Stir in flour and salt.
Knead dough 10 times.
Pinch off 12 pieces. Roll into "worms".
Shape or twist.
Place on greased baking sheet pan. Brush each shape with beaten egg.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter in bottom of dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: purple lady salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in blueberries and pineapple.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold whipped cream and pecans into thickened gelatin.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: potato supreme
directions: Saute bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Drain bacon on paper towels.
Crumble and set aside.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix everything.
May need to thin mixture with nuts.
Add milk to thin.

title: apricot cream cheese delight(salad)
directions: Combine jello, water and pineapple and heat until mixture simmers.
Add sugar, apricot and beaten cream cheese.
Chill until mixture mounds when dropped from a spoon.
Combine Cool Whip and apricot mixture.
Cover with nuts.
Chill.

title: applesauce loaf cake(2nd. place winner, 1980)
directions: Mix and sift first seven ingredients.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually; continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Stir in applesauce.
Add sifted dry ingredients; stir only enough to blend.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan 9 x5 x3-inch.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly touched with fingertip.
Cool in pan 5 mintes. Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Frost, if desired.

title: red wine vinaigrette
directions: Combine red wine vinegar, garlic, parsley and mustard in a bowl and mix well.
Add olive oil slowly while mixing, until incorporated.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Enough for two salads.

title: hurry-up chicken stir-fry
directions: Pour 1 tablespoon oil into wok or large skillet, coating bottom and sides; heat to medium high (325°) for 2 minutes.
Add broccoli and next 4 ingredients; stir-fry 4 minutes.
Remove vegetables from skillet.
Pour remaining 1 tablespoon oil into wok.
Add chicken; stir-fry 4 minutes or until tender.
Return vegetables to wok; stir in salad dressing, soy sauce and ginger. Serve over rice.
Yields 3 servings.

title: tomato-mushroom bow tie pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.

title: no crust cheese cake
directions: Drain crushed pineapple and save about 1/4 cup of the juice. Blend in blender, pineapple juice, lemon juice, egg, vanilla, sugar and gelatine.
Blend well.
Add cottage cheese a little at a time until all is added.
Blend well until mixture is smooth. Pour into a baking dish.
Put pineapple on top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Chill well and cut and serve.

title: nautical pasta
directions: Cook all pasta	al
dente.
Drain in colander and rinse under cold water.
Keep
separate.
Saute
all seafood quickly in butter.
Do not
brown.
Pour
the lemon juice and clams in pan and reduce.
Add
cream
and broccoli.
Lower heat to cook slowly just below	simmering
point.
Do
not boil.
Season to taste with salt and white pepper.
Put cooked pasta in pan and slowly mix with a
spoon until it blends with sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream; blend well.
Stir in mayonnaise and soup mix; add seasonings.
Drain and squeeze dry spinach; gently stir in spinach.

title: cherry-angel pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Mix and spread over bottom and sides of crust of pie.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: curly mint tea
directions: Pour boiling water over mint.
Cover and let steep 10 minutes. Make a gallon of Lipton sun tea with 2 large tea bags.
Strain mint infusion and mix with sun tea.
Add sugar and add lemon juice to taste.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in flour and melted butter.
Mix well.
Turn into greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: sunny broccoli salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Refrigerate and enjoy!

title: baked beans
directions: Soak overnight 1 to 1 1/2 pounds brown beans or kidney beans. In morning, cook until tender; about 2 hours, drain.
Add 1 large bottle catsup, 1/2 box brown sugar, 1 teaspoon mustard, onion and 4 pieces of bacon cut small.
Bake in oven until bubbly, about 1 hour at 325°.
Don't cover.

title: corn pudding
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except tortillas.
Cut tortillas in fourths and layer in casserole alternately with meat mixture until all is used.
Top with cheese.

title: penne alla vodka(yield:  4-6 servings)
directions: 1. In a large skillet, melt butter, add garlic and cook until golden.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, put cake mix, cherry filling, extract and eggs.
Stir the mixture by hand until well blended. Pour into greased 12 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: a good walnut cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sift flour and baking powder.
Put oleo and granulated sugar in mixing bowl. Beat on high 2 minutes. Add egg yolks to creamed mixture and beat until light and fluffy. Add flour and milk, beating until just combined. Add vanilla.
Pour cookie mix in pan, smoothing in pan. Place on center rack in oven and bake 20 minutes. Beat egg whites in small bowl at high speed until stiff. Gradually add brown sugar, beating well.
Pour egg whites into smaller bowl. Fold nuts into brown sugar mixture. Spread over baked cookie crust.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Cut into bars when cooled.
Makes 16 bar cookies.

title: christmas cheese ring
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Form in the shape of a ring.
Decorate it with slices of pimento to make it look like a Christmas wreath. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: fried spaghetti
directions: Boil and drain spaghetti.
Put butter in frying pan and add spaghetti.
Mix 2 eggs into spaghetti.
Cook until done and add salt and pepper.
Add cheese slices on top.
Cover with lid until cheese melts completely.

title: cottage cheese bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked chicken breast supreme
directions: Cut chicken in half, rinse and wipe dry.
In a large bowl combine all ingredients, except chicken, bread crumbs, butter and shortening.
Add chicken, coating each piece well.
Marinate overnight.

title: feather pancakes
directions: In mixing bowl thoroughly stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk and cooking oil; add all at once to dry ingredients, beating until blended.
Bake in hot, lightly greased griddle.
Makes about 32 dollar size pancakes or about 6 to 8 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: rich silver cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add shortening, milk and flavoring.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans. (Batter may appear curdled.)
Bake at 350° until done in 9-inch pans for 30 to 35 minutes, in 8-inch pans bake 25 to 30 minutes, or 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan bake for 1 hour.

title: garlic linguini
directions: Cook breast in boiling water until tender.
Save broth and cut chicken into bite size pieces, set aside.
Cook linguini by package directions, drain and set aside.
Place the butter, spices, vegetables and chicken into a skillet and saute.
After vegetables are crisp tender, add the broth and heat.
Add the drained linguini to the vegetable mix and stir.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Heat broth and milk together; don't boil.
Heat fat in large saucepan.
Add flour to make smooth paste.
Add hot broth slowly. Cook over low heat until very thick.
Beat eggs.
Add small amount of hot mixture to eggs.
Beat in and add all to broth.
Cook 3 to 4 more minutes.
(Optional:
add ground giblets.)
Put in buttered dish layered:
1/2 dressing mixture, 1/2 thickened broth, 1/2 dressing and 1/2 broth.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: italian chicken with garlic and lemon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange chicken in ovenproof pan. In a large skillet, fry the potatoes until golden brown. Save a half cup of frying oil to add to vinegar mixture. Arrange around chicken in pan. Combine all ingredients, including reserved frying oil. Pour over chicken and potatoes. Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours, basting ever so often with the sauce mixture.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine cereal, nuts, raisins and baking powder.
Stir in brown sugar.
Mix milk, egg whites and oil together and blend with cereal mixture.
Line muffin pans with baking cups and fill with batter.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Test doneness with toothpick; it should come out moist, but not wet.
Makes 12 muffins.
Store in plastic bag to retain moisture.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Brown patties.
Mix other ingredients and pour over patties in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: hot egg malted milk
directions: Make a paste of malted milk and boiling water.
Add beaten egg and milk; beat until smooth.
Serve with nutmeg.
May be served cold.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt butter. Sprinkle crumbs over butter; pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over the crumbs. Layer evenly with remaining ingredients. Press down firmly with a fork. Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Cut into bars.

title: corn balls
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and celery in butter until entirely tender; set aside to cool.
In bowl, combine croutons, corn, eggs, water, salt and onion mixture; mix well.
Shape into 8 to 10 balls.
Place in ungreased shallow baking dish, uncovered, at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: onion rings
directions: Heat fat.
Slice onions and separate into rings.
Mix rest of ingredients until smooth.
Dip rings into batter, then drop into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: pan barbecue
directions: In iron Dutch oven, brown beef and onion over high heat in the bacon drippings.
Combine the remaining ingredients except bouillon.
Pour over the meat; add bouillon and blend.
Cover tightly; place in oven at 250° and cook 3 hours.
Serve as is with rice and/or beans.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Mix and heat all of the ingredients except the top round.
Add the steak and marinate all day, turning frequently.
When ready to barbeque, broil 20 minutes on each side.

title: broccoli cheddar soup
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Add broth and milk all at once.
Cook until thick.
Add broccoli; simmer and stir.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese until melted.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together in medium mixing bowl, except flour.
Sift flour in a separate bowl and make a hole in the flour by pushing up the sides.
Pour the mixture into the center of the flour.
Mix with fork until dough is stiff.
Pour onto wax paper and roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters. Nuts or coconut are optional.
Bake until brown.

title: mother's carrot casserole
directions: Place carrots in casserole dish.
Saute onion and celery in oleo until onions are transparent.
Pour this over carrots. Cover with thick slices of Velveeta.
Bake at 250° until melted. Serves 6.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips in a sauce pan.
Butter 4 pieces of foil.
Sprinkle with the sugar or coconut.
Add pecans and marshmallows to chocolate mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Divide mixture into four equal portions.
Shape on foil into rolls.
Turn roll so as to cover with sugar or coconut.	Roll foil around mixture and chill or freeze until firm.
To serve, slice in 1/2-inch slices.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Cook pudding according to directions.
Set aside to cool; beat egg and add oil.
Add egg and oil mixture to cooled pudding.
Use large bowl.
Add mixture to cake mix.
Beat until smooth.
Mixture will be rather thick.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle top of cake mixture evenly with chips and nuts. Bake 36 minutes at 300°.
Bake longer if necessary, but do not raise temperature of oven.

title: marmalade nut bread(blue ribbon winner at la paz county fair)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, orange juice and marmalade.
Mix. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: potato cabbage soup
directions: Cut up; cover with water and cook.
Don't drain water.
Add 1 pound Velveeta cheese (Mexican), cubed, and cook until creamy. Add corned beef.

title: sausage bread
directions: Roll out bread dough (any recipe).
Spread Italian sausage (seasoned with parsley, oregano and pepper) over dough.
Sprinkle on Mozzarella, then Longhorn cheese.
Roll and bake according to bread recipe.

title: meat balls and spaghetti
directions: Soak bread in water and then squeeze out.
Mix remaining ingredients with bread.
Make balls.
Brown meat balls in 2 tablespoons oil; set aside.

title: indonesian pate
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients together and shape into low mound.
Spread chutney over the cheese and cover with the minced green onions.
Serve with Wheat Thins. Serves 12 to 16.

title: company's comin' egg casserole
directions: Tear bread into small pieces. Drain chilies and pimento. Mix all ingredients together. Place in greased 9 x 13 casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve and enjoy!

title: jellied chicken
directions: Slightly grease a custard cup and place the hard-cooked egg slices
in the bottom.
Sprinkle parsley on sides of cup. Pour
in 1/4
cup
of the chicken jelly and chill.	Stand the large slices
of	egg
against the sides of the cup and place smaller slices
in the center.
Mix the chicken and peas with the remaining
jelly
and
pour
into
the
cup on top of egg slices. Chill until firm.
Unmold and serve on a lettuce leaf with desired garnishes.	Exchanges: 3 meat exchanges.

title: green herb dip
directions: *Green Herb seasoning is a salt-free product of the Heart Healthy Kitchen, P.O. Box 4375, Wilmington, DE

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook 8 ounces macaroni.
Drain well and add other ingredients. Chill for about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried eggrolls
directions: In a wok or large skillet, heat oil.
Saute garlic until brown; add chopped onions, then add the chicken and shrimp. Stir-fry vegetables until half cooked.
Drain in a colander and set aside until cooled.
Separate the wrappers.
Put 1 1/2 to 2 tablespoons of meat/vegetable mixture in each wrapper and wrap, folding both sides.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Do not cover to prevent sogginess.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, milk and vanilla. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix in large bowl.
Add crushed pineapples, Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well and chill before serving. Refrigerate.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt and stir the first 4 ingredients until the right color (golden brown), about 15 minutes.
Pour on cookie sheet that has foil and peanuts on it.
Break up after cool.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions and butter.
Put in casserole dish.
Add milk and cheese.
Top with Ritz crackers and butter.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil butter, milk, cocoa and sugar mixture 1 minute.
Remove from heat; mix in vanilla, peanut butter and cooking oats.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: chicken enchiladas verdes(low-fat)
directions: Combine chicken, green onions, garlic powder and 3 tablespoons Salsa Verde.
Mix well.
Heat 1/4 cup chicken broth, until hot, in a small pan.
Slip tortilla shells in pan; heat until soft.
Drain on paper towel.
Fill each shell with 3 tablespoons of chicken mixture.
Roll up and place, seams down, in shallow baking pan. Pour Salsa Verde over shells.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine egg white and water; add nuts and toss to coat. Combine sugar and spices.
Toss in mixture.
Place in single layer on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Remove and cool on wax paper.
Break in small pieces.
Keeps well in airtight container.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Cook on medium heat until mixture thickens.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour over pie.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Place ingredients in layers in a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes and serve with Tostitos chips.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Blend cheeses and egg; spread on bread.
Place an asparagus on end of bread slice and roll up.
Dip in melted butter; place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, cut into 4 or 5 pieces and store in plastic bag in freezer.
(Use metal spatula to remove each roll from cookie sheet; cut on bread board.)
When desired, bake undefrosted at 400° for 10 minutes, until browned.

title: chocolate angel cake dessert
directions: Make a very stiff, glossy meringue with 1/2 cup sugar, 1/8 teaspoon cream of tartar and 2 egg whites.
Reserve about 1/4 of meringue for the crown.
Fold 3/4 cup of finely chopped walnuts into remaining meringue.
Place three 8-inch waxed paper circles on ungreased baking sheete.
Spread each circle with 1/4 of meringue & nut mixture.
For the crown, drop plain meringue from the spoon (or force through a pastry tube) on to waxed paper, Forming 10 or 12 small meringues.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool Peel off the paper carefully

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix spaghetti, Parmesan cheese and eggs together.
Make crust out of mix.
Spread cottage cheese on spaghetti.
Top with meat sauce.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes, or until thoroughly hot. Sprinkle cheese on top and cook 5 minutes more.

title: one-dish chicken dinner
directions: Layer half the potatoes in 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with pepper and lightly salt.
Top with chicken, then peas and then remaining potatoes.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Heat through.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and cover.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cut potatoes, add chopped onion.
Bring to a boil in water that covers potatoes good.
Reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are very tender.
Add soup and cheese to potato mixture. (Do not drain potatoes.)
Mix well and cook until cheese is melted. Serve with bacon bits and chopped green onions added to each bowl. Crackers or cornbread are a must with this soup.

title: egg-ham baked souffle
directions: Trim crust off bread, butter and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Put into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over bread cubes.
Put cubed ham over cheese.
Beat the eggs; add milk and salt.
Pour egg mixture over ham, cheese and bread.
Set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until cheese puffs up over the ham.
Serves 8.
(Bread mixture should be no higher than 3/4 full.)

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix bran and boiling water.
Cool.
Beat shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Add bran to mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add dry ingredients to mixture until mixed well.
Stir in bran buds and pour into muffin pan.	Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
May be kept in refrigerator for 4 to 6 weeks and baked as needed.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water in large mixing bowl. Stir until dissolved. Add shortening, salt and half the flour.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Gradually add remaining flour, mixing with hands until dough is stiff and leaves side of bowl. Turn dough out onto floured board.
Cover with bowl. Let rest 10 minutes. Knead 8 to 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic. Place dough in lightly greased medium bowl. Cover with towel and let raise in warm place, about 1 hour.

title: honey coated ham and vegetables
directions: Chop up the first 6 ingredients.
Mix them all together in a large bowl.
Add the pepper and Italian seasoning.
Pour the oil and honey over the mixture.
Use a spoon to mix/blend all the ingredients.
Spread the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Sift ingredients in an ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Make 3 holes, 1 tablespoon vinegar in one, 6 tablespoons salad oil in next and 1 tablespoon vanilla in last one.
Pour 3/4 cup applesauce and 1/2 cup water over holes.
Mix well with fork.
If using unsweetened applesauce, you may add more sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Nuts and raisins can be added.

title: cranberry salad
directions: For a Fruit Slaw:
Cabbage, apples, pineapple, raisins, etc. Beat sweet cider into Miracle Whip to desired consistency.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs, then gradually add in the sugar.
Beat in oil. Mix together the dry ingredients and add alternately with zucchini to egg mixture.
Stir in raisins, walnuts and vanilla.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans at 350° for 55 minutes. Allow to cool before removing from pans.
Cool before cutting. May be iced with confectioners sugar and water glaze.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut and mix all ingredients in large bowl.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in eggs one at a time.
Stir in rolled oats.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
If you love pecan pie, you will like oatmeal pie.

title: shower punch
directions: Stir together the boiling water, jello and sugar.
Dissolve in orange juice, lemonade, and pineapple juice.
Add the gallon water; stir well.
Freeze for at least 24 hours.
When ready to use, set out 2 to 3 hours ahead of time to serve as a slush.
Add 3 bottles of ginger ale to slush punch in a large punch bowl. Serves 50 people.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together until fluffy.
Add the dry ingredients; mix well.
Add oil, vanilla and apples; mix well. Bake at 350° in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes.

title: pork 'n kraut(crockery cooking)
directions: Boil pork for 1/2 hour.
Put apples and rest of ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir.
Cut pork into serving size pieces and add to pot.
Turn on low and cook for 6 to 8 hours (until pork is tender).

title: crab biscayne
directions: Break crabmeat into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients. Mix lightly with fork.
Pile into scallop shells.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place meat (don't brown) on bottom of large casserole dish. Add potatoes, carrots, onions, peas, stir in salt and pepper. Cover with tomato soup.
Bake covered 250 for 7 hours.
Works well in crock pot also, low temp for 8 - 10 hours.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: While browning ground beef and onion, put the Tater Tots in oven on a cookie sheet; brown lightly.
Spray a 9 x 12-inch baking dish with Pam.
Put in pan 1 layer of the browned Tater Tots.
I mix the 2 cans soup with the ground beef and onion after draining off the fat; pour beef-soup mixture over bottom layer of Tater Tots.
Put remaining Tater Tots on top of mixture.
Cover top of casserole with shredded cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: snowballs
