directions: Cream together sugar and softened margarine. Add pineapple, pecans and vanilla. Mix together well. Spread between 3 cookies. Freeze 24 hours, covered.

title: lemon whipped cream pie
directions: Fold whipped cream into lemon mixture.
Pour into pie shell and add some of the crumbled nuts on top for garnish.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: Remove leaves and core from cauliflower and steam the whole head until tender.
Make a sauce by melting the butter, and adding the flour to blend.
Add the milk and cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper.
Add the pimiento, ham, or both and heat through.
Add the cheese and stir until melted.
To serve, place the steamed cauliflower in a bowl or dish and pour the sauce over it.
This makes a very nice centerpiece dish.
Be sure the cauliflower is not over cooked so it will stay together as a whole center.

title: lemon delight
directions: Cut butter
into
flour.
Stir	in
1/2 cup nuts; press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place tortillas in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole. Add chicken. In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients except cheese. Pour over chicken. Top with grated cheese. Bake 30 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: purple cow
directions: Put ice cream in blender.
Add milk and grape juice.
Liquify until smooth.

title: strawberry fluff pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, gelatin, water and lemon juice in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it comes to a boil. Pour into a bowl and chill until thick.
Fold in prepared whip topping, blend well.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour in pie shell and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Garnish with topping and strawberries if you like.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, salt and mustard in mixing bowl using low speed.
Add onion and small amount of vinegar and mix well.
Add oil and remaining vinegar slowly, beating constantly.
Now add celery seed.
Mix well.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Wipe spareribs with damp cloth.
Cut into serving size pieces. Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook all vegetables in 1 1/2 cups water.
Dissolve bouillon cube in other 1/2 cup water.
Make milk and flour mixture smooth, then combine this mixture and bouillon cube mixture with vegetables until soup thickens.
Then add cheese and ham.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: pralines
directions: Cook until soft ball forms in cold water.
Take from stove and add vanilla and pecans.
Beat.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: fresh coconut layer cake
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Add cream of tartar and soda to flour and sift.
Beat egg yolks until very light; add sugar.
Add vanilla to coconut milk.
Alternate flour and coconut milk to sugar.
Fold in whites, beaten
stiff.
This makes 4 layers.
Bake for 30 minutes in moderate oven.
Ice with Fresh Coconut Icing.

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Combine tapioca, honey, salt, water, milk, vanilla, flour, baking powder and 3 tablespoon butter in a saucepan.
Cook until mixture boils.
Stir constantly.
Add lemon juice, blueberries and 1 tablespoon of butter.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Ladle into sherbet glasses.
Cool and serve.

title: butter cookies
directions: Whip butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and whip until very light.
Add flour gradually and beat until mixed well.
Add vanilla and blend well.

title: irish bread #2
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and caraway seed.
Cut in butter until consistency of coarse meal.
Stir in raisins.
Combine buttermilk, 1 egg and baking soda.
Stir wet mixture into dry mixture just to moisten. Knead until smooth.
Shape into ball and place in a greased 9-inch round pan.
Press to fill pan.
Cut slashes (+) in center.
Brush with egg yolk.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; place on rack.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger slowly in large skillet.
In another pan, cook onions, mangos or celery until tender.
Drain fat off hamburger and add onion mixture.
Add salt, pepper and chili sauce.
Rinse bottle with water and add to mixture.
Add rest of ingredients and cook slowly for 45 minutes.
If mixture is too thick, add ketchup; or water.

title: chicken barbecue sauce 2
directions: In large kettle, beat egg and add oil.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Cook and stir over high heat.
(Stir constantly or egg will curdle.)
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Add chicken to this; cover and simmer until chicken is almost done.
Remove from sauce and barbecue on grill using sauce to baste or use this only as a basting sauce for barbecue chicken on grill.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add flavorings and eggs.
Beat well.
Add oats, flour, soda and salt.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet and bake until brown at 350°.

title: picadillo(pik-uh-dee'yo)
directions: Heat the oil in a Dutch oven or stew pot and add the onions. Saute until the onions are golden, but not black, about 10 minutes.
Add the beef and break up into small pieces as it browns.
Add the tomato sauce and mix well.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook gently, stirring occasionally, until the meat is cooked through and flavors are blended, about 15 minutes. Taste for seasoning.
Add salt and pepper to taste, and more vinegar, if necessary.
Serves 2 with leftovers.
Serve over a bed of white rice.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese; cut into flour and salt.
Divide dough.
Roll half on lightly floured board.
Place in bottom of pie plate.
Roll out remainder of dough and set aside for top.

title: balsamic chicken
directions: Dust chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown 2 minutes in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low 30 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread chicken over butter.
Then spread veggies over chicken.
Mix broth and soup; pour over all.
(This can be done ahead of time at this point and refrigerated.)
Then mix milk and Bisquick.
Batter will be thin.
Pour this over entire dish.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mama's egg custard
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add other ingredients.
Blend together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn oven to 325° and bake 30 more minutes.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan.
Simmer over low heat until cheese melts.
Mix well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: the philly 3-step cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients at medium speed until well blended.
Blend in eggs.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Pour batter into pie crust.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup mini semi-sweet chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool.
For best results, refrigerate for 3 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: american chop suey
directions: Cook pasta (elbows) as directed.
Brown hamburg and onion in heavy skillet; drain fat.
Add tomatoes (chopped) and tomato soup. Simmer while waiting for pasta.
Drain cooked pasta and add to tomato and beef mixture.
Simmer.
Add salt and pepper and sprinkle celery salt to taste.
Enjoy!

title: punch
directions: Mix Jell-O the regular way; bring to boil the sugar and water. Add to Jell-O mixture; add the juice of 2 lemons.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: geraldine's chocolate cake(makes 3 or 4 layers)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well between each egg.
Alternate flour and buttermilk.
Sift salt and soda with flour before alternating with milk.
Cook at 350° until light brown.

title: chewy pecan squares
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and mix real good.
Add pecans.	Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: sugar coated pecans
directions: Lightly toast pecans at 300° for 10 minutes.
Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and salt.
Cook over low heat until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Then add vanilla and pecans.
Cook until mixture starts to become dry.
Remove from heat and pour nuts on tray to separate and cool.

title: crispy date balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla, cereal and pecans.
Cool to touch.

title: veg-all
directions: Melt
1/2 stick oleo with Cheez Whiz.
Mix in Veg-All.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt the other 1/2 stick oleo with crushed Ritz and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350°
for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: fudgies
directions: Combine skim milk powder, soy powder and carob in medium size bowl; add oil and honey.
Stir in hot water, then nuts and vanilla.
Form into balls and roll in nuts.
Can be refrigerated.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift salt and pepper with flour; fold in butter.
Let cheese be at room temperature.
Work cheese until smooth into flour mixture.
Run through a cookie press or cut in desired lengths. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until they are firm to the touch (so that they are crisp).

title: winter turkey salad
directions: Mix together and put in a greased casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup crushed plain potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: jalapeno squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain off water.
Stir all ingredients together.
Put into buttered casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and more grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry-walnut cake
directions: Heat the oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. In a large bowl, using wire whisk, stir the first 4 ingredients until well blended. Combine the eggs, oil, milk and vanilla and whisk them in. Stir in cranberries and walnuts and turn into the prepared pan. Sprinkle top with sugar. Bake until cake is golden brown and shrinking from the pan. Let cake cool in pan and then cut into squares. Makes about 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: sausage and stuffing
directions: Melt butter with water.
Stir in stuffing. Add egg and sausage.
Blend with hands. Chill 1 hour or so.
Shape into balls. Cut bacon in thirds.
Wrap and insert toothpick.
Cook at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pies
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed.
Soften cream cheese, beat with powdered sugar.
Blend prepared Dream Whip into cheese mixture.
Spoon into 2 unbaked graham cracker crumb crusts. Chill 2 hours or more.
Top with canned cherry pie filling.

title: herb crescent rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and fill rolls with this mixture. Roll them in melted butter and dressing mix.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes or until golden.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in oleo.
Slice and brown Polish sausages.
Add pork and beans, barbecue sauce, brown sugar and mustard.
Cook on low for 2 to 3 hours in crock-pot.

title: strawberry philly pie
directions: Bake pastry shell 5 minutes in a 425° oven.
Cream the cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sugar.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and vanilla.
Slowly add to the cream cheese mixture, stirring until well blended.
Pour into pastry shell.
Put in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool pie.
Add strawberry jam over top and whipped cream just before serving.

title: stuffed pasta bake
directions: Combine Ricotta cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, garlic and parsley flakes; mix well.

title: green limas in squash nest
directions: Mash squash.
Season.
Whip until light and place in individual mounds on greased cookie sheet.
Make a hollow in center of each mound and fill with seasoned lima beans.
Heat in moderate oven (350°).
Serves 4.

title: butter mint salad
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan, pour the 2 cans of crushed pineapple. Sprinkle dry lime jello on top of pineapple.
Top with bag of marshmallows and let stand in the refrigerator overnight.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Combine cream cheese, soup and remaining ingredients, except biscuits, in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place biscuits on top of casserole.
Bake again for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach bake
directions: Preheat toaster oven at 350° for 2 minutes.
Layer one half zucchini into bottom of small casserole.
Cover with one half tomato slices, one half pepper slices and 3 slices cheese.
Repeat layers.
Dot surface with butter.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until zucchini is tender.
Serves 6.

title: pawley's island crab cakes
directions: In a large bowl, combine well the mayonnaise, cracker crumbs, cayenne, celery seed, mustard, lemon juice and egg whites and stir in the crab meat gently.
Form the mixture into 12 half-inch thick cakes and coat the cakes with most of the bread crumbs.
Sprinkle a large plate with the remaining bread crumbs; transfer the crab cakes to the plate and chill them, covered loosely, for at least 1 hour and up to 4 hours.

In a large heavy skillet, heat the butter over moderately high heat until it is hot but not smoking and in it, saute the crab cakes, turning them once, for 4 minutes per side or until they are golden.
As the crab cakes are cooked, use a slotted spoon to transfer them to drain on paper towels, then arrange them on a heated platter.
Garnish the cakes with lemon wedges and serve them with tartar sauce.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend 30 seconds.
Makes 2 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Save 1/4 cup grease.
Cook onion in grease until tender.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and a dash of pepper.
Add vinegar and 1 cup water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add bacon and potatoes (eggs); heat thoroughly.

title: watkins homemade syrup
directions: Combine.
Boil all ingredients for 1 minute.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Arrange in layers as follows: cabbage, pepper, onions and pimento. Do not stir.

title: sunday chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Combine and stir thoroughly in large bowl cream of chicken soup, cream of celery soup, cream of mushroom soup (or creamy onion soup), water and melted margarine.
Pour 1/2 mixture into another bowl and add raw rice (not instant rice). Pour this (rice and soup) into bottom of 12 x 8-inch Pyrex dish which has been lightly greased with margarine.
Place cut up fryer on top of rice and soup mixture, then pour the other half of soup mixture on top of chicken pieces, covering each piece.
Bake in 275° oven 2 1/2 to 3 hours, depending on size of chicken (in open dish).

title: frito soup
directions: Soak pinto beans in water for 3 hours.
Simmer soup bones, celery, onion, peppercorns and salt with beans for 3 hours. Remove bones and add stewed tomatoes, whole tomatoes, green chilies and chili powder.
Simmer 2 hours.
Serve with Doritos or Fritos, crumbled in bottom of bowl and topped with grated Mozzarella cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla and zucchini. Add dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix with next four ingredients.
Let simmer for about 30 minutes.
Line bottom of casserole dish with 1/2 of the crushed Doritos.
Pour 1/2 the meat mixture over it. Cover with 1/2 the shredded cheese.
Repeat process.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: In frying pan, brown both sides of pork chops.
In crock-pot, mix soup and milk.
Add browned pork chops.
Cook on high for 3 hours.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together butter, flour and pecans.
Put in an 11 x 14-inch pan or dish at 350° until light brown.
Mix together sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on cool crust, then top with 1 can cherry pie filling.
Cool 2 hours before serving.

title: apple butter layer cake
directions: Stir together flour, salt, soda, spices, raisins and walnuts. Beat butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat eggs, one at a time.
Combine buttermilk and apple butter.
Add alternately with flour mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool thoroughly.
Frost with Creamy Vanilla Frosting.

title: banana split cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
When cake is cool, cover with vanilla instant pudding mixed with milk and cream cheese. Cover with pineapple and banana slices.
Cover well with Cool Whip.
Decorate with maraschino cherries and nuts, if desired.

title: homemade cocoa mix
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine all ingredients.
Blend well. Store in tightly covered container.
To use single serving; combine 1/4 cup mix and 3/4 cup of boiling water in cup or mug.
Stir to blend.
Makes 3-1/4 cups (15-16 servings).

title: spinach rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook rice as directed.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add cooked rice, cheese, salt and parsley.
Fold in spinach.
Pour into casserole.

title: zippy pork barbecue sandwiches
directions: In Dutch oven, combine meat and water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, approximately 2 hours or until meat is very tender.
Remove meat from broth, reserving 1/2 cup broth. Return broth to Dutch oven and add onion and celery.
Cook, covered, for approximately 10 minutes or until vegetables are very tender.
Stir in brown sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire, vinegar, mustard and pepper.
Remove meat from the bones and discard fat and bones.
Chop or shred remaining meat.
Add meat to mixture in Dutch oven and simmer until warmed up enough to eat.
Spoon onto buns and enjoy!

title: mushroom canapes
directions: Clean mushrooms; cut in small pieces.
Saute mushrooms in butter for about 10 minutes.
Add lemon juice, sour cream and enough paprika to tint pink.
Mix well.
Place 1 teaspoon of mixture on each piece of bread.
Broil for 5 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot.
Yields 40 canapes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix.
Layer in large container, lettuce, tomato, ground beef mixture, drained kidney beans and shredded cheese.
Just before serving add crushed tortilla chips; top with Russian dressing and serve.

title: easy chicken parmesan(serves 4. always juicy and tender)
directions: Dip chicken breasts in eggs until well coated.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese and mix well.
Roll each chicken breast in dry mixture until well coated.
Place in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour margarine on top of chicken.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: liver sausage ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in bowl.
Decorate with sliced olives.
Serve with crackers or party bread.

title: crumb pies (cake)
directions: Mix sugar, lard and flour together.
Set aside 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Add remaining dry ingredients to mixture.
Beat in eggs and milk.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to scalded milk that has been cooled.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and work into dough.
Knead dough 15 to 20 times and set aside to rest for 10 minutes.
Roll dough to 1/4 inch thickness or slightly thinner.
Cut into squares or triangles and fry in deep fryer at 420°.
Fry only 2 at a time, so the oil stays hot.
If the oil is hot, the sopaipillas will puff up and become hollow shortly after they have been added to the oil.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.

title: reindeer cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well and set aside.
Cut a graham cracker diagonally in half using a gentle sawing motion with a serrated knife.
Spread a small amount of frosting over top side of cracker half.
Top with remaining cracker half, placing cut sides opposite each other so 2 narrow ends meet to form reindeer nose.
Spread a small amount of frosting to cover top cracker.
Gently press chocolate morsels on reindeer for eyes and cinnamon candy for nose.
Add pretzel halves for antlers. Repeat procedure to use remaining ingredients.
Let dry on a wire rack. Yields 1 dozen.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.
Pie is done when top is golden brown and knife inserted in middle of pie comes out clean.

title: onion salad dressing
directions: Mix well.
Add slowly 1 cup of salad oil.
Add it last.
Whip with spoon as oil is added.
Dry ingredients added first.

title: beans, peas and corn salad
directions: Bring the last 3 ingredients to a boil and boil 1 minute. Pour over the rest of the ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste. It will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: blt puffs
directions: Combine 1 cup water and the butter in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil. The butter should be melted by this time.
Remove from heat immediately.
This is an important step in order for the puffs to work.
You don't want to reduce the amount of water by boiling.
Combine the flour and spaghetti sauce mix.
Add the flour mixture to the water mixture all at once and stir until blended.
Return to heat to dry the mixture a little, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool slightly for about 5 minutes.

Add 4 eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Each time you add an egg and start to beat, the mixture will separate slightly and begin to look like Southern dumplings. Keep beating until the mixtures pulls together and looks like mashed potatoes.
Drop small mounds (about 3/4 inch in diameter) from a teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Puff will triple when baked.
Combine the 1 teaspoon water with the remaining egg and beat until blended.
Brush each puff with this mixture.
Wait about 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 400 degrees for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely before filling.

title: peach chess pie
directions: Peel peaches and cut in half.
Place in bottom of unbaked pie shell with cavity side down.
The number of peaches you use depends on their size.
Beat sugar and butter or margarine.
Work flour into this mixture (I mix the flour with the sugar, it is easier that way), then beat in egg until blended.
Add vanilla and stir to blend.
Spread over top of peaches.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Puncture the crust that has formed on top of the pie.
Lower heat to 300° and bake an additional 30 minutes. Custard should be slightly firm.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding until well blended.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: congealed salad
directions: Cream the jello and cream cheese just like you would butter and sugar.
Add 1 cup of hot water.
Chill until soft set.
Whip Carnation milk; whip into jello.
Add pineapple (juice too) and nuts.
Refrigerate until set.
Serves 6 or less, depending on how well you like it.

title: fried cheese
directions: Dip cheese cubes in eggs.
Coat with crumbs; repeat.
Fry in hot oil (350° to 375°) until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.

title: cinnamony apple streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Combine graham cracker crumbs, flour, 1/2 c. brown sugar, granulated sugar, cinnamon and melted butter in large bowl until well blended; reserve 1 c. Press remaining crumb mixture into bottom of prepared pan. Bake 8 minutes. remove from oven; set aside. Toss apples with remaining 1/4 c. brown sugar in medium bowl until brown sugar is dissolved; arrange apples over baked crust. Sprinkle reserved 1 c. crumb mixture over filling. Bake 30 to 35 minutes more or until apples are tender. Remove pan to wire rack; cool completely. Drizzle with glaze. Cut into bars. Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place on low heat while making crust. Place mixture in crust.
Weave lattice on top and brush with butter.
Place foil collar on fluted edges until last 10 minutes of baking.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry tarte
directions: Beat together and pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Cover with blueberry or cherry pie filling.

title: divinity salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add the sauce and mix.
Chill and serve.

title: walnut dream bars
directions: Mix together the butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup sifted flour.
Pat smooth in an 8 x 8-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix together the pineapple, cherries and nuts; set aside. Cream together the butter, sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add in the fruit and 1 egg at a time while mixing.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes until brown.

title: berry butters
directions: With an electric mixer, beat pureed berries into softened butter until blended.
Beat in sugar, blending well.
Pack into small serving bowl or into chilled butter mold.
Serve on pancakes, waffles, muffins or fresh baked bread.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: Blend eggs, oil, vanilla and sugar.
Mix in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine salt, sugar, flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and allspice.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Prepare meatballs by directions on back of French's mix.
In large saucepan, mix the jelly, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce together.
Cook over medium-high heat until jelly is dissolved. After meatballs are fried, add them to the sauce.
Mix and simmer until hot.

title: linda twelves' chicken marinade
directions: Cover chicken completely.
Marinate 24 hours.
Bake or grill chicken.

title: raspberry glazed chicken(lo-cal)
directions: Place chicken on the rack of a broiler pan coated with cooking spray. Sprinkle salt and pepper evenly over chicken. Broil chicken for 7 minutes. Turn chicken; baste with 2 tablespoons raspberry spread and broil 10 minutes longer or until chicken is done. Combine 2 tablespoons raspberry spread and 1 teaspoon water in a 1-cup glass measure. Microwave on HIGH 30 seconds; spoon mixture evenly over chicken.

title: "melomakarona" - honey dipped cookies
directions: Mix all together in order given.
Use enough flour to make a medium soft dough easy to handle and shape.
Shape into oblongs. Brush with a beaten egg yolk and sprinkle with sesame seed, if desired.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and beef.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: deer or elk sausage
directions: Mix spices together and gradually mix with meat.
Refrigerate for 4 days, mixing every day.
On the fifth day, shape into salami rolls.
Put on broiler rack in broiler pan.
Cook for 8 hours at 140° in bottom shelf of oven.
Will form its own crust.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth. Pour into chilled bowls.
Garnish.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: sherried fruit
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Add water, lemon juice and sliced peaches.
Poach peaches slowly and baste them frequently with syrup.
Cook until fruit is still firm but cooked through (5 minutes).
Add sherry at the end. Serve hot with meat or warm with cream for dessert. You may substitute apples, pears, canned pineapple or cherries for the peaches.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Just put all the ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix ingredients well; roll into eggs.
Freeze (1 hour), then dip in melted chocolate.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Mix together the sugar, vinegar and oil; pour over beans and onion.

title: green chile
directions: Sprinkle chops with flour and brown in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with tortillas or pour over burritos and top with cheese, sour cream and guacamole.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat cookie dough into a 14-inch pizza pan or cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and pineapple juice.
Spread on crust.
Add fruit of any type.

title: pecan patties
directions: Saute onion in a little oil.
Combine all ingredients except mushroom sauce.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and brown on both sides.
Place in casserole and cover with sauce.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 25 minutes.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into pan.

title: grilled fruit with poppy seed dressing
directions: Poppy Seed Dressing:
Mix poppy seed, sour cream, 1/8 cup honey, caramel topping, brandy and lemon juice.

title: clara's cheese ball
directions: Crush vegetables in package with rolling pin. Add to cream cheese. Mix the crushed vegetables and onion into the softened cream cheese. Form ball. Roll in nuts of choice. Refrigerate.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill 5-quart crock-pot heaping full with finely chopped apples.
Drizzle sugar over top.
Sprinkle on spices and salt. Cover.
Lid will go down as they heat.
Begin cooking on high, then lower heat and cook all day until thick and dark.
Stir occasionally.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick and clear.
Add gelatin; cook until completely dissolved.
Put strawberries into baked pie crust.
Pour syrup over strawberries and chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: strawberry preserves from figs
directions: Mash figs and add dry Jell-O, then add sugar.
Stir well.
Let stand for 30 minutes; stir.
Heat slowly to a boil.
Stir frequently.
Simmer an extra 5 minutes.
Pour into sterile jars.

title: green tomato relish
directions: First, put chopped tomatoes in large pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup salt; let set 1 hour or longer.
Can leave overnight; stir occasionally.
Put through colander to get all juice off tomatoes. Mix all together.
Cook slow until tender, 20 or 30 minutes.
Check often so as not to overcook.
Seal in jars.

title: super potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in dish (ovenproof).
Cover with cream and cheese.
Let melt and brown in oven.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese
and butter in heavy bottomed saucepan. Stir over low heat until soft, butter melted and thoroughly blended.
Add powdered sugar and stir until well combined.
Add your choice of food coloring and flavoring.
You may divide whole batch to make 2 to 3 choices.
Add extract to taste.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on sheet of waxed paper.
Press with fork or stamp with decorative cookie stamp.
Let stand uncovered about 4 hours or overnight until mints are firm and outside is dry, but inside is moist and creamy.

title: super simple sheet cake
directions: Pour oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; tilt pan until oil covers bottom.
Combine cake mix, eggs and water in pan; stir with fork until blended (about 2 minutes).
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Serve plain or with fresh strawberries or peaches and cream.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: To slightly beaten eggs, add sugar, flour, salt and spices. Stir thoroughly.
Add pumpkin and stir again.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into prepared pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 minutes longer, or until a silver knife comes out clean when inserted in filling.

title: tuna-bean salad
directions: Combine tuna, beans, celery, green pepper, pickles, pimiento, onion and mayonnaise.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and chill thoroughly, at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serves 6.

title: 30 day friendship cake
directions: Combine and then leave in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Cook peaches down in about 1/4 cup of sugar (according to tartness of fruit) and a dash of cinnamon.

title: rice-sausage casserole
directions: Saute vegetables.
Prepare soup, using 1/2 water called for in package directions.
Add soup, rice and sausage to vegetables and simmer a few minutes.
Place in casserole dish and top with almonds and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Freezes beautifully.

title: ranch beans
directions: Melt butter. Brown hamburger, drain. Stir in soup mix and all other ingredients. Bake in a 2 qt. skillet at 400 degrees for 30-40 minutes. Can put in a crock pot and let it simmer quite awhile. This is great for a potluck!

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook grated zucchini and 6 cups sugar.
Boil 6 minutes, add crushed pineapple and boil 6 minutes more.
Remove from heat and add 2 small packages apricot jello.
Stir well.
Bottle.
Makes 5 pints.

title: low-fat egg kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until glossy.
Fold in cereal and chocolate chips.
Spray cookie sheets with Pam.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 325° for 14 to 46 minutes.

title: tiny marmalade biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix marmalade and butter; spread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Stir baking mix and water to a soft dough. Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured cloth-covered board. Knead 5 times.
Roll into 8-inch square; place on marmalade-butter mixture in pan.
Pat evenly in corners; cut into 36 squares.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Invert pan on serving plate.
Biscuits will break off into small bite size pieces.
Serve warm.
Can be baked ahead and reheated.

title: vegetable cheese lasagna
directions: Mushroom Layer:
In a 10-inch skillet, heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot; add mushrooms and saute, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are lightly browned and cooked through, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, sift dry ingredients, flour, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon. In another bowl, mix pumpkin, sugar, oil and slightly beaten eggs. Add water and stir well. Add to flour mixture and beat. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. If you like, you may add raisins and chopped nuts.

title: breakfast monkey bread
directions: Prepare Bundt pan.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Layer butterscotch pudding, then pecans.
Dip bread slices in butter, then cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Layer in pan.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool slightly, then invert on warm plate.

title: delicate egg and cheese bake
directions: Beat eggs and salad dressing mix in large bowl.
Stir in cheese, cottage cheese and chopped pepper.
Mix flour with baking powder.
Stir flour mixture and butter into cheese mixture.
Pour into greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes with butter.
Salt when taken out of oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Let cool and pull chicken off bone and place in baking dish.
Pour soup over chicken and spread evenly.
Then pour milk over this, spreading evenly also.
